3021static struct sk_buff *validate_xmit_vlan(struct sk_buff *skb,
3022 netdev_features_t features)
3023{
3024 if (skb_vlan_tag_present(skb) &&
3025 !vlan_hw_offload_capable(features, skb->vlan_proto))
3026 skb = __vlan_hwaccel_push_inside(skb);
3027 return skb;
3028}
3029
3030int skb_csum_hwoffload_help(struct sk_buff *skb,
3031 const netdev_features_t features)
3032{
3033 if (unlikely(skb->csum_not_inet))
3034 return !!(features & NETIF_F_SCTP_CRC) ? 0 :
3035 skb_crc32c_csum_help(skb);
3036
3037 return !!(features & NETIF_F_CSUM_MASK) ? 0 : skb_checksum_help(skb);
3038}
3039EXPORT_SYMBOL(skb_csum_hwoffload_help);
3040
3041static struct sk_buff *validate_xmit_skb(struct sk_buff *skb, struct net_device *dev)
3042{
3043 netdev_features_t features;
3044
3045 features = netif_skb_features(skb);
3046 skb = validate_xmit_vlan(skb, features);
3047 if (unlikely(!skb))
3048 goto out_null;
3049
3050 if (netif_needs_gso(skb, features)) {
3051 struct sk_buff *segs;
3052
3053 segs = skb_gso_segment(skb, features);
3054 if (IS_ERR(segs)) {
3055 goto out_kfree_skb;
3056 } else if (segs) {
3057 consume_skb(skb);
3058 skb = segs;
3059 }
3060 } else {
3061 if (skb_needs_linearize(skb, features) &&
3062 __skb_linearize(skb))
3063 goto out_kfree_skb;
3064
3065 if (validate_xmit_xfrm(skb, features))
3066 goto out_kfree_skb;
3067
3068 /* If packet is not checksummed and device does not
3069 * support checksumming for this protocol, complete
3070 * checksumming here.
3071 */
3072 if (skb->ip_summed == CHECKSUM_PARTIAL) {
3073 if (skb->encapsulation)
3074 skb_set_inner_transport_header(skb,
3075 skb_checksum_start_offset(skb));
3076 else
3077 skb_set_transport_header(skb,
3078 skb_checksum_start_offset(skb));
3079 if (skb_csum_hwoffload_help(skb, features))
3080 goto out_kfree_skb;
3081 }
3082 }
3083
3084 return skb;
3085
3086out_kfree_skb:
3087 kfree_skb(skb);
3088out_null:
3089 atomic_long_inc(&dev->tx_dropped);
3090 return NULL;
3091}
3092
3093struct sk_buff *validate_xmit_skb_list(struct sk_buff *skb, struct net_device *dev)
3094{
3095 struct sk_buff *next, *head = NULL, *tail;
3096
3097 for (; skb != NULL; skb = next) {
3098 next = skb->next;
3099 skb->next = NULL;
3100
3101 /* in case skb wont be segmented, point to itself */
3102 skb->prev = skb;
3103
3104 skb = validate_xmit_skb(skb, dev);
3105 if (!skb)
3106 continue;
3107
3108 if (!head)
3109 head = skb;
3110 else
3111 tail->next = skb;
3112 /* If skb was segmented, skb->prev points to
3113 * the last segment. If not, it still contains skb.
3114 */
3115 tail = skb->prev;
3116 }
3117 return head;
3118}
3119EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(validate_xmit_skb_list);
3120
3121static void qdisc_pkt_len_init(struct sk_buff *skb)
3122{
3123 const struct skb_shared_info *shinfo = skb_shinfo(skb);
3124
3125 qdisc_skb_cb(skb)->pkt_len = skb->len;
3126
3127 /* To get more precise estimation of bytes sent on wire,
3128 * we add to pkt_len the headers size of all segments
3129 */
3130 if (shinfo->gso_size) {
3131 unsigned int hdr_len;
3132 u16 gso_segs = shinfo->gso_segs;
3133
3134 /* mac layer + network layer */
3135 hdr_len = skb_transport_header(skb) - skb_mac_header(skb);
3136
3137 /* + transport layer */
3138 if (likely(shinfo->gso_type & (SKB_GSO_TCPV4 | SKB_GSO_TCPV6))) {
3139 const struct tcphdr *th;
3140 struct tcphdr _tcphdr;
3141
3142 th = skb_header_pointer(skb, skb_transport_offset(skb),
3143 sizeof(_tcphdr), &_tcphdr);
3144 if (likely(th))
3145 hdr_len += __tcp_hdrlen(th);
3146 } else {
3147 struct udphdr _udphdr;
3148
3149 if (skb_header_pointer(skb, skb_transport_offset(skb),
3150 sizeof(_udphdr), &_udphdr))
3151 hdr_len += sizeof(struct udphdr);
3152 }
3153
3154 if (shinfo->gso_type & SKB_GSO_DODGY)
3155 gso_segs = DIV_ROUND_UP(skb->len - hdr_len,
3156 shinfo->gso_size);
3157
3158 qdisc_skb_cb(skb)->pkt_len += (gso_segs - 1) * hdr_len;
3159 }
3160}
3161
3162static inline int __dev_xmit_skb(struct sk_buff *skb, struct Qdisc *q,
3163 struct net_device *dev,
3164 struct netdev_queue *txq)
3165{
3166 spinlock_t *root_lock = qdisc_lock(q);
3167 struct sk_buff *to_free = NULL;
3168 bool contended;
3169 int rc;
3170
3171 qdisc_calculate_pkt_len(skb, q);
3172 /*
3173 * Heuristic to force contended enqueues to serialize on a
3174 * separate lock before trying to get qdisc main lock.
3175 * This permits qdisc->running owner to get the lock more
3176 * often and dequeue packets faster.
3177 */
3178 contended = qdisc_is_running(q);
3179 if (unlikely(contended))
3180 spin_lock(&q->busylock);
3181
3182 spin_lock(root_lock);
3183 if (unlikely(test_bit(__QDISC_STATE_DEACTIVATED, &q->state))) {
3184 __qdisc_drop(skb, &to_free);
3185 rc = NET_XMIT_DROP;
3186 } else if ((q->flags & TCQ_F_CAN_BYPASS) && !qdisc_qlen(q) &&
3187 qdisc_run_begin(q)) {
3188 /*
3189 * This is a work-conserving queue; there are no old skbs
3190 * waiting to be sent out; and the qdisc is not running -
3191 * xmit the skb directly.
3192 */
3193
3194 qdisc_bstats_update(q, skb);
3195
3196 if (sch_direct_xmit(skb, q, dev, txq, root_lock, true)) {
3197 if (unlikely(contended)) {
3198 spin_unlock(&q->busylock);
3199 contended = false;
3200 }
3201 __qdisc_run(q);
3202 } else
3203 qdisc_run_end(q);
3204
3205 rc = NET_XMIT_SUCCESS;
3206 } else {
3207 rc = q->enqueue(skb, q, &to_free) & NET_XMIT_MASK;
3208 if (qdisc_run_begin(q)) {
3209 if (unlikely(contended)) {
3210 spin_unlock(&q->busylock);
3211 contended = false;
3212 }
3213 __qdisc_run(q);
3214 }
3215 }
3216 spin_unlock(root_lock);
3217 if (unlikely(to_free))
3218 kfree_skb_list(to_free);
3219 if (unlikely(contended))
3220 spin_unlock(&q->busylock);
3221 return rc;
3222}

3224#if IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_CGROUP_NET_PRIO)
3225static void skb_update_prio(struct sk_buff *skb)
3226{
3227 const struct netprio_map *map;
3228 const struct sock *sk;
3229 unsigned int prioidx;
3230
3231 if (skb->priority)
3232 return;
3233 map = rcu_dereference_bh(skb->dev->priomap);
3234 if (!map)
3235 return;
3236 sk = skb_to_full_sk(skb);
3237 if (!sk)
3238 return;
3239
3240 prioidx = sock_cgroup_prioidx(&sk->sk_cgrp_data);
3241
3242 if (prioidx < map->priomap_len)
3243 skb->priority = map->priomap[prioidx];
3244}
3245#else
3246#define skb_update_prio(skb)
3247#endif

3252/**
3253 * dev_loopback_xmit - loop back @skb
3254 * @net: network namespace this loopback is happening in
3255 * @sk: sk needed to be a netfilter okfn
3256 * @skb: buffer to transmit
3257 */
3258int dev_loopback_xmit(struct net *net, struct sock *sk, struct sk_buff *skb)
3259{
3260 skb_reset_mac_header(skb);
3261 __skb_pull(skb, skb_network_offset(skb));
3262 skb->pkt_type = PACKET_LOOPBACK;
3263 skb->ip_summed = CHECKSUM_UNNECESSARY;
3264 WARN_ON(!skb_dst(skb));
3265 skb_dst_force(skb);
3266 netif_rx_ni(skb);
3267 return 0;
3268}
3269EXPORT_SYMBOL(dev_loopback_xmit);

3271#ifdef CONFIG_NET_EGRESS
3272static struct sk_buff *
3273sch_handle_egress(struct sk_buff *skb, int *ret, struct net_device *dev)
3274{
3275 struct tcf_proto *cl = rcu_dereference_bh(dev->egress_cl_list);
3276 struct tcf_result cl_res;
3277
3278 if (!cl)
3279 return skb;
3280
3281 /* qdisc_skb_cb(skb)->pkt_len was already set by the caller. */
3282 qdisc_bstats_cpu_update(cl->q, skb);
3283
3284 switch (tcf_classify(skb, cl, &cl_res, false)) {
3285 case TC_ACT_OK:
3286 case TC_ACT_RECLASSIFY:
3287 skb->tc_index = TC_H_MIN(cl_res.classid);
3288 break;
3289 case TC_ACT_SHOT:
3290 qdisc_qstats_cpu_drop(cl->q);
3291 *ret = NET_XMIT_DROP;
3292 kfree_skb(skb);
3293 return NULL;
3294 case TC_ACT_STOLEN:
3295 case TC_ACT_QUEUED:
3296 case TC_ACT_TRAP:
3297 *ret = NET_XMIT_SUCCESS;
3298 consume_skb(skb);
3299 return NULL;
3300 case TC_ACT_REDIRECT:
3301 /* No need to push/pop skb's mac_header here on egress! */
3302 skb_do_redirect(skb);
3303 *ret = NET_XMIT_SUCCESS;
3304 return NULL;
3305 default:
3306 break;
3307 }
3308
3309 return skb;
3310}
3311#endif /* CONFIG_NET_EGRESS */
3312
3313static inline int get_xps_queue(struct net_device *dev, struct sk_buff *skb)
3314{
3315#ifdef CONFIG_XPS
3316 struct xps_dev_maps *dev_maps;
3317 struct xps_map *map;
3318 int queue_index = -1;
3319
3320 rcu_read_lock();
3321 dev_maps = rcu_dereference(dev->xps_maps);
3322 if (dev_maps) {
3323 unsigned int tci = skb->sender_cpu - 1;
3324
3325 if (dev->num_tc) {
3326 tci *= dev->num_tc;
3327 tci += netdev_get_prio_tc_map(dev, skb->priority);
3328 }
3329
3330 map = rcu_dereference(dev_maps->cpu_map[tci]);
3331 if (map) {
3332 if (map->len == 1)
3333 queue_index = map->queues[0];
3334 else
3335 queue_index = map->queues[reciprocal_scale(skb_get_hash(skb),
3336 map->len)];
3337 if (unlikely(queue_index >= dev->real_num_tx_queues))
3338 queue_index = -1;
3339 }
3340 }
3341 rcu_read_unlock();
3342
3343 return queue_index;
3344#else
3345 return -1;
3346#endif
3347}
3348
3349static u16 __netdev_pick_tx(struct net_device *dev, struct sk_buff *skb)
3350{
3351 struct sock *sk = skb->sk;
3352 int queue_index = sk_tx_queue_get(sk);
3353
3354 if (queue_index < 0 || skb->ooo_okay ||
3355 queue_index >= dev->real_num_tx_queues) {
3356 int new_index = get_xps_queue(dev, skb);
3357
3358 if (new_index < 0)
3359 new_index = skb_tx_hash(dev, skb);
3360
3361 if (queue_index != new_index && sk &&
3362 sk_fullsock(sk) &&
3363 rcu_access_pointer(sk->sk_dst_cache))
3364 sk_tx_queue_set(sk, new_index);
3365
3366 queue_index = new_index;
3367 }
3368
3369 return queue_index;
3370}
3371
3372struct netdev_queue *netdev_pick_tx(struct net_device *dev,
3373 struct sk_buff *skb,
3374 void *accel_priv)
3375{
3376 int queue_index = 0;
3377
3378#ifdef CONFIG_XPS
3379 u32 sender_cpu = skb->sender_cpu - 1;
3380
3381 if (sender_cpu >= (u32)NR_CPUS)
3382 skb->sender_cpu = raw_smp_processor_id() + 1;
3383#endif
3384
3385 if (dev->real_num_tx_queues != 1) {
3386 const struct net_device_ops *ops = dev->netdev_ops;
3387
3388 if (ops->ndo_select_queue)
3389 queue_index = ops->ndo_select_queue(dev, skb, accel_priv,
3390 __netdev_pick_tx);
3391 else
3392 queue_index = __netdev_pick_tx(dev, skb);
3393
3394 if (!accel_priv)
3395 queue_index = netdev_cap_txqueue(dev, queue_index);
3396 }
3397
3398 skb_set_queue_mapping(skb, queue_index);
3399 return netdev_get_tx_queue(dev, queue_index);
3400}
3401
3402/**
3403 * __dev_queue_xmit - transmit a buffer
3404 * @skb: buffer to transmit
3405 * @accel_priv: private data used for L2 forwarding offload
3406 *
3407 * Queue a buffer for transmission to a network device. The caller must
3408 * have set the device and priority and built the buffer before calling
3409 * this function. The function can be called from an interrupt.
3410 *
3411 * A negative errno code is returned on a failure. A success does not
3412 * guarantee the frame will be transmitted as it may be dropped due
3413 * to congestion or traffic shaping.
3414 *
3415 * -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3416 * I notice this method can also return errors from the queue disciplines,
3417 * including NET_XMIT_DROP, which is a positive value. So, errors can also
3418 * be positive.
3419 *
3420 * Regardless of the return value, the skb is consumed, so it is currently
3421 * difficult to retry a send to this method. (You can bump the ref count
3422 * before sending to hold a reference for retry if you are careful.)
3423 *
3424 * When calling this method, interrupts MUST be enabled. This is because
3425 * the BH enable code must have IRQs enabled so that it will not deadlock.
3426 * --BLG
3427 */
3428static int __dev_queue_xmit(struct sk_buff *skb, void *accel_priv)
3429{
3430 struct net_device *dev = skb->dev;
3431 struct netdev_queue *txq;
3432 struct Qdisc *q;
3433 int rc = -ENOMEM;
3434
3435 skb_reset_mac_header(skb);
3436
3437 if (unlikely(skb_shinfo(skb)->tx_flags & SKBTX_SCHED_TSTAMP))
3438 __skb_tstamp_tx(skb, NULL, skb->sk, SCM_TSTAMP_SCHED);
3439
3440 /* Disable soft irqs for various locks below. Also
3441 * stops preemption for RCU.
3442 */
3443 rcu_read_lock_bh();
3444
3445 skb_update_prio(skb);
3446
3447 qdisc_pkt_len_init(skb);
3448#ifdef CONFIG_NET_CLS_ACT
3449 skb->tc_at_ingress = 0;
3450# ifdef CONFIG_NET_EGRESS
3451 if (static_key_false(&egress_needed)) {
3452 skb = sch_handle_egress(skb, &rc, dev);
3453 if (!skb)
3454 goto out;
3455 }
3456# endif
3457#endif
3458 /* If device/qdisc don't need skb->dst, release it right now while
3459 * its hot in this cpu cache.
3460 */
3461 if (dev->priv_flags & IFF_XMIT_DST_RELEASE)
3462 skb_dst_drop(skb);
3463 else
3464 skb_dst_force(skb);
3465
3466 txq = netdev_pick_tx(dev, skb, accel_priv);
3467 q = rcu_dereference_bh(txq->qdisc);
3468
3469 trace_net_dev_queue(skb);
3470 if (q->enqueue) {
3471 rc = __dev_xmit_skb(skb, q, dev, txq);
3472 goto out;
3473 }
3474
3475 /* The device has no queue. Common case for software devices:
3476 * loopback, all the sorts of tunnels...
3477
3478 * Really, it is unlikely that netif_tx_lock protection is necessary
3479 * here. (f.e. loopback and IP tunnels are clean ignoring statistics
3480 * counters.)
3481 * However, it is possible, that they rely on protection
3482 * made by us here.
3483
3484 * Check this and shot the lock. It is not prone from deadlocks.
3485 *Either shot noqueue qdisc, it is even simpler 8)
3486 */
3487 if (dev->flags & IFF_UP) {
3488 int cpu = smp_processor_id(); /* ok because BHs are off */
3489
3490 if (txq->xmit_lock_owner != cpu) {
3491 if (unlikely(__this_cpu_read(xmit_recursion) >
3492 XMIT_RECURSION_LIMIT))
3493 goto recursion_alert;
3494
3495 skb = validate_xmit_skb(skb, dev);
3496 if (!skb)
3497 goto out;
3498
3499 HARD_TX_LOCK(dev, txq, cpu);
3500
3501 if (!netif_xmit_stopped(txq)) {
3502 __this_cpu_inc(xmit_recursion);
3503 skb = dev_hard_start_xmit(skb, dev, txq, &rc);
3504 __this_cpu_dec(xmit_recursion);
3505 if (dev_xmit_complete(rc)) {
3506 HARD_TX_UNLOCK(dev, txq);
3507 goto out;
3508 }
3509 }
3510 HARD_TX_UNLOCK(dev, txq);
3511 net_crit_ratelimited("Virtual device %s asks to queue packet!\n",
3512 dev->name);
3513 } else {
3514 /* Recursion is detected! It is possible,
3515 * unfortunately
3516 */
3517recursion_alert:
3518 net_crit_ratelimited("Dead loop on virtual device %s, fix it urgently!\n",
3519 dev->name);
3520 }
3521 }
3522
3523 rc = -ENETDOWN;
3524 rcu_read_unlock_bh();
3525
3526 atomic_long_inc(&dev->tx_dropped);
3527 kfree_skb_list(skb);
3528 return rc;
3529out:
3530 rcu_read_unlock_bh();
3531 return rc;
3532}
3533
3534int dev_queue_xmit(struct sk_buff *skb)
3535{
3536 return __dev_queue_xmit(skb, NULL);
3537}
3538EXPORT_SYMBOL(dev_queue_xmit);
3539
3540int dev_queue_xmit_accel(struct sk_buff *skb, void *accel_priv)
3541{
3542 return __dev_queue_xmit(skb, accel_priv);
3543}
3544EXPORT_SYMBOL(dev_queue_xmit_accel);

3551int netdev_max_backlog __read_mostly = 1000;
3552EXPORT_SYMBOL(netdev_max_backlog);
3553
3554int netdev_tstamp_prequeue __read_mostly = 1;
3555int netdev_budget __read_mostly = 300;
3556unsigned int __read_mostly netdev_budget_usecs = 2000;
3557int weight_p __read_mostly = 64; /* old backlog weight */
3558int dev_weight_rx_bias __read_mostly = 1; /* bias for backlog weight */
3559int dev_weight_tx_bias __read_mostly = 1; /* bias for output_queue quota */
3560int dev_rx_weight __read_mostly = 64;
3561int dev_tx_weight __read_mostly = 64;

3563/* Called with irq disabled */
3564static inline void ____napi_schedule(struct softnet_data *sd,
3565 struct napi_struct *napi)
3566{
3567 list_add_tail(&napi->poll_list, &sd->poll_list);
3568 __raise_softirq_irqoff(NET_RX_SOFTIRQ);
3569}

3571#ifdef CONFIG_RPS
3572
3573/* One global table that all flow-based protocols share. */
3574struct rps_sock_flow_table __rcu *rps_sock_flow_table __read_mostly;
3575EXPORT_SYMBOL(rps_sock_flow_table);
3576u32 rps_cpu_mask __read_mostly;
3577EXPORT_SYMBOL(rps_cpu_mask);
3578
3579struct static_key rps_needed __read_mostly;
3580EXPORT_SYMBOL(rps_needed);
3581struct static_key rfs_needed __read_mostly;
3582EXPORT_SYMBOL(rfs_needed);
3583
3584static struct rps_dev_flow *
3585set_rps_cpu(struct net_device *dev, struct sk_buff *skb,
3586 struct rps_dev_flow *rflow, u16 next_cpu)
3587{
3588 if (next_cpu < nr_cpu_ids) {
3589#ifdef CONFIG_RFS_ACCEL
3590 struct netdev_rx_queue *rxqueue;
3591 struct rps_dev_flow_table *flow_table;
3592 struct rps_dev_flow *old_rflow;
3593 u32 flow_id;
3594 u16 rxq_index;
3595 int rc;
3596
3597 /* Should we steer this flow to a different hardware queue? */
3598 if (!skb_rx_queue_recorded(skb) || !dev->rx_cpu_rmap ||
3599 !(dev->features & NETIF_F_NTUPLE))
3600 goto out;
3601 rxq_index = cpu_rmap_lookup_index(dev->rx_cpu_rmap, next_cpu);
3602 if (rxq_index == skb_get_rx_queue(skb))
3603 goto out;
3604
3605 rxqueue = dev->_rx + rxq_index;
3606 flow_table = rcu_dereference(rxqueue->rps_flow_table);
3607 if (!flow_table)
3608 goto out;
3609 flow_id = skb_get_hash(skb) & flow_table->mask;
3610 rc = dev->netdev_ops->ndo_rx_flow_steer(dev, skb,
3611 rxq_index, flow_id);
3612 if (rc < 0)
3613 goto out;
3614 old_rflow = rflow;
3615 rflow = &flow_table->flows[flow_id];
3616 rflow->filter = rc;
3617 if (old_rflow->filter == rflow->filter)
3618 old_rflow->filter = RPS_NO_FILTER;
3619 out:
3620#endif
3621 rflow->last_qtail =
3622 per_cpu(softnet_data, next_cpu).input_queue_head;
3623 }
3624
3625 rflow->cpu = next_cpu;
3626 return rflow;
3627}
3628
3629/*
3630 * get_rps_cpu is called from netif_receive_skb and returns the target
3631 * CPU from the RPS map of the receiving queue for a given skb.
3632 * rcu_read_lock must be held on entry.
3633 */
3634static int get_rps_cpu(struct net_device *dev, struct sk_buff *skb,
3635 struct rps_dev_flow **rflowp)
3636{
3637 const struct rps_sock_flow_table *sock_flow_table;
3638 struct netdev_rx_queue *rxqueue = dev->_rx;
3639 struct rps_dev_flow_table *flow_table;
3640 struct rps_map *map;
3641 int cpu = -1;
3642 u32 tcpu;
3643 u32 hash;
3644
3645 if (skb_rx_queue_recorded(skb)) {
3646 u16 index = skb_get_rx_queue(skb);
3647
3648 if (unlikely(index >= dev->real_num_rx_queues)) {
3649 WARN_ONCE(dev->real_num_rx_queues > 1,
3650 "%s received packet on queue %u, but number "
3651 "of RX queues is %u\n",
3652 dev->name, index, dev->real_num_rx_queues);
3653 goto done;
3654 }
3655 rxqueue += index;
3656 }
3657
3658 /* Avoid computing hash if RFS/RPS is not active for this rxqueue */
3659
3660 flow_table = rcu_dereference(rxqueue->rps_flow_table);
3661 map = rcu_dereference(rxqueue->rps_map);
3662 if (!flow_table && !map)
3663 goto done;
3664
3665 skb_reset_network_header(skb);
3666 hash = skb_get_hash(skb);
3667 if (!hash)
3668 goto done;
3669
3670 sock_flow_table = rcu_dereference(rps_sock_flow_table);
3671 if (flow_table && sock_flow_table) {
3672 struct rps_dev_flow *rflow;
3673 u32 next_cpu;
3674 u32 ident;
3675
3676 /* First check into global flow table if there is a match */
3677 ident = sock_flow_table->ents[hash & sock_flow_table->mask];
3678 if ((ident ^ hash) & ~rps_cpu_mask)
3679 goto try_rps;
3680
3681 next_cpu = ident & rps_cpu_mask;
3682
3683 /* OK, now we know there is a match,
3684 * we can look at the local (per receive queue) flow table
3685 */
3686 rflow = &flow_table->flows[hash & flow_table->mask];
3687 tcpu = rflow->cpu;
3688
3689 /*
3690 * If the desired CPU (where last recvmsg was done) is
3691 * different from current CPU (one in the rx-queue flow
3692 * table entry), switch if one of the following holds:
3693 * - Current CPU is unset (>= nr_cpu_ids).
3694 * - Current CPU is offline.
3695 * - The current CPU's queue tail has advanced beyond the
3696 * last packet that was enqueued using this table entry.
3697 * This guarantees that all previous packets for the flow
3698 * have been dequeued, thus preserving in order delivery.
3699 */
3700 if (unlikely(tcpu != next_cpu) &&
3701 (tcpu >= nr_cpu_ids || !cpu_online(tcpu) ||
3702 ((int)(per_cpu(softnet_data, tcpu).input_queue_head -
3703 rflow->last_qtail)) >= 0)) {
3704 tcpu = next_cpu;
3705 rflow = set_rps_cpu(dev, skb, rflow, next_cpu);
3706 }
3707
3708 if (tcpu < nr_cpu_ids && cpu_online(tcpu)) {
3709 *rflowp = rflow;
3710 cpu = tcpu;
3711 goto done;
3712 }
3713 }
3714
3715try_rps:
3716
3717 if (map) {
3718 tcpu = map->cpus[reciprocal_scale(hash, map->len)];
3719 if (cpu_online(tcpu)) {
3720 cpu = tcpu;
3721 goto done;
3722 }
3723 }
3724
3725done:
3726 return cpu;
3727}
3728
3729#ifdef CONFIG_RFS_ACCEL
3730
3731/**
3732 * rps_may_expire_flow - check whether an RFS hardware filter may be removed
3733 * @dev: Device on which the filter was set
3734 * @rxq_index: RX queue index
3735 * @flow_id: Flow ID passed to ndo_rx_flow_steer()
3736 * @filter_id: Filter ID returned by ndo_rx_flow_steer()
3737 *
3738 * Drivers that implement ndo_rx_flow_steer() should periodically call
3739 * this function for each installed filter and remove the filters for
3740 * which it returns %true.
3741 */
3742bool rps_may_expire_flow(struct net_device *dev, u16 rxq_index,
3743 u32 flow_id, u16 filter_id)
3744{
3745 struct netdev_rx_queue *rxqueue = dev->_rx + rxq_index;
3746 struct rps_dev_flow_table *flow_table;
3747 struct rps_dev_flow *rflow;
3748 bool expire = true;
3749 unsigned int cpu;
3750
3751 rcu_read_lock();
3752 flow_table = rcu_dereference(rxqueue->rps_flow_table);
3753 if (flow_table && flow_id <= flow_table->mask) {
3754 rflow = &flow_table->flows[flow_id];
3755 cpu = ACCESS_ONCE(rflow->cpu);
3756 if (rflow->filter == filter_id && cpu < nr_cpu_ids &&
3757 ((int)(per_cpu(softnet_data, cpu).input_queue_head -
3758 rflow->last_qtail) <
3759 (int)(10 * flow_table->mask)))
3760 expire = false;
3761 }
3762 rcu_read_unlock();
3763 return expire;
3764}
3765EXPORT_SYMBOL(rps_may_expire_flow);
3766
3767#endif /* CONFIG_RFS_ACCEL */
3768
3769/* Called from hardirq (IPI) context */
3770static void rps_trigger_softirq(void *data)
3771{
3772 struct softnet_data *sd = data;
3773
3774 ____napi_schedule(sd, &sd->backlog);
3775 sd->received_rps++;
3776}
3777
3778#endif /* CONFIG_RPS */
3779
3780/*
3781 * Check if this softnet_data structure is another cpu one
3782 * If yes, queue it to our IPI list and return 1
3783 * If no, return 0
3784 */
3785static int rps_ipi_queued(struct softnet_data *sd)
3786{
3787#ifdef CONFIG_RPS
3788 struct softnet_data *mysd = this_cpu_ptr(&softnet_data);
3789
3790 if (sd != mysd) {
3791 sd->rps_ipi_next = mysd->rps_ipi_list;
3792 mysd->rps_ipi_list = sd;
3793
3794 __raise_softirq_irqoff(NET_RX_SOFTIRQ);
3795 return 1;
3796 }
3797#endif /* CONFIG_RPS */
3798 return 0;
3799}
3800
3801#ifdef CONFIG_NET_FLOW_LIMIT
3802int netdev_flow_limit_table_len __read_mostly = (1 << 12);
3803#endif
3804
3805static bool skb_flow_limit(struct sk_buff *skb, unsigned int qlen)
3806{
3807#ifdef CONFIG_NET_FLOW_LIMIT
3808 struct sd_flow_limit *fl;
3809 struct softnet_data *sd;
3810 unsigned int old_flow, new_flow;
3811
3812 if (qlen < (netdev_max_backlog >> 1))
3813 return false;
3814
3815 sd = this_cpu_ptr(&softnet_data);
3816
3817 rcu_read_lock();
3818 fl = rcu_dereference(sd->flow_limit);
3819 if (fl) {
3820 new_flow = skb_get_hash(skb) & (fl->num_buckets - 1);
3821 old_flow = fl->history[fl->history_head];
3822 fl->history[fl->history_head] = new_flow;
3823
3824 fl->history_head++;
3825 fl->history_head &= FLOW_LIMIT_HISTORY - 1;
3826
3827 if (likely(fl->buckets[old_flow]))
3828 fl->buckets[old_flow]--;
3829
3830 if (++fl->buckets[new_flow] > (FLOW_LIMIT_HISTORY >> 1)) {
3831 fl->count++;
3832 rcu_read_unlock();
3833 return true;
3834 }
3835 }
3836 rcu_read_unlock();
3837#endif
3838 return false;
3839}
3840
3841/*
3842 * enqueue_to_backlog is called to queue an skb to a per CPU backlog
3843 * queue (may be a remote CPU queue).
3844 */
3845static int enqueue_to_backlog(struct sk_buff *skb, int cpu,
3846 unsigned int *qtail)
3847{
3848 struct softnet_data *sd;
3849 unsigned long flags;
3850 unsigned int qlen;
3851
3852 sd = &per_cpu(softnet_data, cpu);
3853
3854 local_irq_save(flags);
3855
3856 rps_lock(sd);
3857 if (!netif_running(skb->dev))
3858 goto drop;
3859 qlen = skb_queue_len(&sd->input_pkt_queue);
3860 if (qlen <= netdev_max_backlog && !skb_flow_limit(skb, qlen)) {
3861 if (qlen) {
3862enqueue:
3863 __skb_queue_tail(&sd->input_pkt_queue, skb);
3864 input_queue_tail_incr_save(sd, qtail);
3865 rps_unlock(sd);
3866 local_irq_restore(flags);
3867 return NET_RX_SUCCESS;
3868 }
3869
3870 /* Schedule NAPI for backlog device
3871 * We can use non atomic operation since we own the queue lock
3872 */
3873 if (!__test_and_set_bit(NAPI_STATE_SCHED, &sd->backlog.state)) {
3874 if (!rps_ipi_queued(sd))
3875 ____napi_schedule(sd, &sd->backlog);
3876 }
3877 goto enqueue;
3878 }
3879
3880drop:
3881 sd->dropped++;
3882 rps_unlock(sd);
3883
3884 local_irq_restore(flags);
3885
3886 atomic_long_inc(&skb->dev->rx_dropped);
3887 kfree_skb(skb);
3888 return NET_RX_DROP;
3889}
3890
3891static u32 netif_receive_generic_xdp(struct sk_buff *skb,
3892 struct bpf_prog *xdp_prog)
3893{
3894 struct xdp_buff xdp;
3895 u32 act = XDP_DROP;
3896 void *orig_data;
3897 int hlen, off;
3898 u32 mac_len;
3899
3900 /* Reinjected packets coming from act_mirred or similar should
3901 * not get XDP generic processing.
3902 */
3903 if (skb_cloned(skb))
3904 return XDP_PASS;
3905
3906 if (skb_linearize(skb))
3907 goto do_drop;
3908
3909 /* The XDP program wants to see the packet starting at the MAC
3910 * header.
3911 */
3912 mac_len = skb->data - skb_mac_header(skb);
3913 hlen = skb_headlen(skb) + mac_len;
3914 xdp.data = skb->data - mac_len;
3915 xdp.data_end = xdp.data + hlen;
3916 xdp.data_hard_start = skb->data - skb_headroom(skb);
3917 orig_data = xdp.data;
3918
3919 act = bpf_prog_run_xdp(xdp_prog, &xdp);
3920
3921 off = xdp.data - orig_data;
3922 if (off > 0)
3923 __skb_pull(skb, off);
3924 else if (off < 0)
3925 __skb_push(skb, -off);
3926 skb->mac_header += off;
3927
3928 switch (act) {
3929 case XDP_REDIRECT:
3930 case XDP_TX:
3931 __skb_push(skb, mac_len);
3932 /* fall through */
3933 case XDP_PASS:
3934 break;
3935
3936 default:
3937 bpf_warn_invalid_xdp_action(act);
3938 /* fall through */
3939 case XDP_ABORTED:
3940 trace_xdp_exception(skb->dev, xdp_prog, act);
3941 /* fall through */
3942 case XDP_DROP:
3943 do_drop:
3944 kfree_skb(skb);
3945 break;
3946 }
3947
3948 return act;
3949}
3950
3951/* When doing generic XDP we have to bypass the qdisc layer and the
3952 * network taps in order to match in-driver-XDP behavior.
3953 */
3954void generic_xdp_tx(struct sk_buff *skb, struct bpf_prog *xdp_prog)
3955{
3956 struct net_device *dev = skb->dev;
3957 struct netdev_queue *txq;
3958 bool free_skb = true;
3959 int cpu, rc;
3960
3961 txq = netdev_pick_tx(dev, skb, NULL);
3962 cpu = smp_processor_id();
3963 HARD_TX_LOCK(dev, txq, cpu);
3964 if (!netif_xmit_stopped(txq)) {
3965 rc = netdev_start_xmit(skb, dev, txq, 0);
3966 if (dev_xmit_complete(rc))
3967 free_skb = false;
3968 }
3969 HARD_TX_UNLOCK(dev, txq);
3970 if (free_skb) {
3971 trace_xdp_exception(dev, xdp_prog, XDP_TX);
3972 kfree_skb(skb);
3973 }
3974}
3975EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(generic_xdp_tx);
3976
3977static struct static_key generic_xdp_needed __read_mostly;
3978
3979int do_xdp_generic(struct bpf_prog *xdp_prog, struct sk_buff *skb)
3980{
3981 if (xdp_prog) {
3982 u32 act = netif_receive_generic_xdp(skb, xdp_prog);
3983 int err;
3984
3985 if (act != XDP_PASS) {
3986 switch (act) {
3987 case XDP_REDIRECT:
3988 err = xdp_do_generic_redirect(skb->dev, skb,
3989 xdp_prog);
3990 if (err)
3991 goto out_redir;
3992 /* fallthru to submit skb */
3993 case XDP_TX:
3994 generic_xdp_tx(skb, xdp_prog);
3995 break;
3996 }
3997 return XDP_DROP;
3998 }
3999 }
4000 return XDP_PASS;
4001out_redir:
4002 kfree_skb(skb);
4003 return XDP_DROP;
4004}
4005EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(do_xdp_generic);
4006
4007static int netif_rx_internal(struct sk_buff *skb)
4008{
4009 int ret;
4010
4011 net_timestamp_check(netdev_tstamp_prequeue, skb);
4012
4013 trace_netif_rx(skb);
4014
4015 if (static_key_false(&generic_xdp_needed)) {
4016 int ret;
4017
4018 preempt_disable();
4019 rcu_read_lock();
4020 ret = do_xdp_generic(rcu_dereference(skb->dev->xdp_prog), skb);
4021 rcu_read_unlock();
4022 preempt_enable();
4023
4024 /* Consider XDP consuming the packet a success from
4025 * the netdev point of view we do not want to count
4026 * this as an error.
4027 */
4028 if (ret != XDP_PASS)
4029 return NET_RX_SUCCESS;
4030 }
4031
4032#ifdef CONFIG_RPS
4033 if (static_key_false(&rps_needed)) {
4034 struct rps_dev_flow voidflow, *rflow = &voidflow;
4035 int cpu;
4036
4037 preempt_disable();
4038 rcu_read_lock();
4039
4040 cpu = get_rps_cpu(skb->dev, skb, &rflow);
4041 if (cpu < 0)
4042 cpu = smp_processor_id();
4043
4044 ret = enqueue_to_backlog(skb, cpu, &rflow->last_qtail);
4045
4046 rcu_read_unlock();
4047 preempt_enable();
4048 } else
4049#endif
4050 {
4051 unsigned int qtail;
4052
4053 ret = enqueue_to_backlog(skb, get_cpu(), &qtail);
4054 put_cpu();
4055 }
4056 return ret;
4057}
4058
4059/**
4060 * netif_rx - post buffer to the network code
4061 * @skb: buffer to post
4062 *
4063 * This function receives a packet from a device driver and queues it for
4064 * the upper (protocol) levels to process. It always succeeds. The buffer
4065 * may be dropped during processing for congestion control or by the
4066 * protocol layers.
4067 *
4068 * return values:
4069 * NET_RX_SUCCESS (no congestion)
4070 * NET_RX_DROP (packet was dropped)
4071 *
4072 */
4073
4074int netif_rx(struct sk_buff *skb)
4075{
4076 trace_netif_rx_entry(skb);
4077
4078 return netif_rx_internal(skb);
4079}
4080EXPORT_SYMBOL(netif_rx);
4081
4082int netif_rx_ni(struct sk_buff *skb)
4083{
4084 int err;
4085
4086 trace_netif_rx_ni_entry(skb);
4087
4088 preempt_disable();
4089 err = netif_rx_internal(skb);
4090 if (local_softirq_pending())
4091 do_softirq();
4092 preempt_enable();
4093
4094 return err;
4095}
4096EXPORT_SYMBOL(netif_rx_ni);
4097
4098static __latent_entropy void net_tx_action(struct softirq_action *h)
4099{
4100 struct softnet_data *sd = this_cpu_ptr(&softnet_data);
4101
4102 if (sd->completion_queue) {
4103 struct sk_buff *clist;
4104
4105 local_irq_disable();
4106 clist = sd->completion_queue;
4107 sd->completion_queue = NULL;
4108 local_irq_enable();
4109
4110 while (clist) {
4111 struct sk_buff *skb = clist;
4112
4113 clist = clist->next;
4114
4115 WARN_ON(refcount_read(&skb->users));
4116 if (likely(get_kfree_skb_cb(skb)->reason == SKB_REASON_CONSUMED))
4117 trace_consume_skb(skb);
4118 else
4119 trace_kfree_skb(skb, net_tx_action);
4120
4121 if (skb->fclone != SKB_FCLONE_UNAVAILABLE)
4122 __kfree_skb(skb);
4123 else
4124 __kfree_skb_defer(skb);
4125 }
4126
4127 __kfree_skb_flush();
4128 }
4129
4130 if (sd->output_queue) {
4131 struct Qdisc *head;
4132
4133 local_irq_disable();
4134 head = sd->output_queue;
4135 sd->output_queue = NULL;
4136 sd->output_queue_tailp = &sd->output_queue;
4137 local_irq_enable();
4138
4139 while (head) {
4140 struct Qdisc *q = head;
4141 spinlock_t *root_lock;
4142
4143 head = head->next_sched;
4144
4145 root_lock = qdisc_lock(q);
4146 spin_lock(root_lock);
4147 /* We need to make sure head->next_sched is read
4148 * before clearing __QDISC_STATE_SCHED
4149 */
4150 smp_mb__before_atomic();
4151 clear_bit(__QDISC_STATE_SCHED, &q->state);
4152 qdisc_run(q);
4153 spin_unlock(root_lock);
4154 }
4155 }
4156}
4157
4158#if IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_BRIDGE) && IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_ATM_LANE)
4159/* This hook is defined here for ATM LANE */
4160int (*br_fdb_test_addr_hook)(struct net_device *dev,
4161 unsigned char *addr) __read_mostly;
4162EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(br_fdb_test_addr_hook);
4163#endif
4164
4165static inline struct sk_buff *
4166sch_handle_ingress(struct sk_buff *skb, struct packet_type **pt_prev, int *ret,
4167 struct net_device *orig_dev)
4168{
4169#ifdef CONFIG_NET_CLS_ACT
4170 struct tcf_proto *cl = rcu_dereference_bh(skb->dev->ingress_cl_list);
4171 struct tcf_result cl_res;
4172
4173 /* If there's at least one ingress present somewhere (so
4174 * we get here via enabled static key), remaining devices
4175 * that are not configured with an ingress qdisc will bail
4176 * out here.
4177 */
4178 if (!cl)
4179 return skb;
4180 if (*pt_prev) {
4181 *ret = deliver_skb(skb, *pt_prev, orig_dev);
4182 *pt_prev = NULL;
4183 }
4184
4185 qdisc_skb_cb(skb)->pkt_len = skb->len;
4186 skb->tc_at_ingress = 1;
4187 qdisc_bstats_cpu_update(cl->q, skb);
4188
4189 switch (tcf_classify(skb, cl, &cl_res, false)) {
4190 case TC_ACT_OK:
4191 case TC_ACT_RECLASSIFY:
4192 skb->tc_index = TC_H_MIN(cl_res.classid);
4193 break;
4194 case TC_ACT_SHOT:
4195 qdisc_qstats_cpu_drop(cl->q);
4196 kfree_skb(skb);
4197 return NULL;
4198 case TC_ACT_STOLEN:
4199 case TC_ACT_QUEUED:
4200 case TC_ACT_TRAP:
4201 consume_skb(skb);
4202 return NULL;
4203 case TC_ACT_REDIRECT:
4204 /* skb_mac_header check was done by cls/act_bpf, so
4205 * we can safely push the L2 header back before
4206 * redirecting to another netdev
4207 */
4208 __skb_push(skb, skb->mac_len);
4209 skb_do_redirect(skb);
4210 return NULL;
4211 default:
4212 break;
4213 }
4214#endif /* CONFIG_NET_CLS_ACT */
4215 return skb;
4216}
4217
4218/**
4219 * netdev_is_rx_handler_busy - check if receive handler is registered
4220 * @dev: device to check
4221 *
4222 * Check if a receive handler is already registered for a given device.
4223 * Return true if there one.
4224 *
4225 * The caller must hold the rtnl_mutex.
4226 */
4227bool netdev_is_rx_handler_busy(struct net_device *dev)
4228{
4229 ASSERT_RTNL();
4230 return dev && rtnl_dereference(dev->rx_handler);
4231}
4232EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(netdev_is_rx_handler_busy);
4233
4234/**
4235 * netdev_rx_handler_register - register receive handler
4236 * @dev: device to register a handler for
4237 * @rx_handler: receive handler to register
4238 * @rx_handler_data: data pointer that is used by rx handler
4239 *
4240 * Register a receive handler for a device. This handler will then be
4241 * called from __netif_receive_skb. A negative errno code is returned
4242 * on a failure.
4243 *
4244 * The caller must hold the rtnl_mutex.
4245 *
4246 * For a general description of rx_handler, see enum rx_handler_result.
4247 */
4248int netdev_rx_handler_register(struct net_device *dev,
4249 rx_handler_func_t *rx_handler,
4250 void *rx_handler_data)
4251{
4252 if (netdev_is_rx_handler_busy(dev))
4253 return -EBUSY;
4254
4255 /* Note: rx_handler_data must be set before rx_handler */
4256 rcu_assign_pointer(dev->rx_handler_data, rx_handler_data);
4257 rcu_assign_pointer(dev->rx_handler, rx_handler);
4258
4259 return 0;
4260}
4261EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(netdev_rx_handler_register);
4262
4263/**
4264 * netdev_rx_handler_unregister - unregister receive handler
4265 * @dev: device to unregister a handler from
4266 *
4267 * Unregister a receive handler from a device.
4268 *
4269 * The caller must hold the rtnl_mutex.
4270 */
4271void netdev_rx_handler_unregister(struct net_device *dev)
4272{
4273
4274 ASSERT_RTNL();
4275 RCU_INIT_POINTER(dev->rx_handler, NULL);
4276 /* a reader seeing a non NULL rx_handler in a rcu_read_lock()
4277 * section has a guarantee to see a non NULL rx_handler_data
4278 * as well.
4279 */
4280 synchronize_net();
4281 RCU_INIT_POINTER(dev->rx_handler_data, NULL);
4282}
4283EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(netdev_rx_handler_unregister);
4284
4285/*
4286 * Limit the use of PFMEMALLOC reserves to those protocols that implement
4287 * the special handling of PFMEMALLOC skbs.
4288 */
4289static bool skb_pfmemalloc_protocol(struct sk_buff *skb)
4290{
4291 switch (skb->protocol) {
4292 case htons(ETH_P_ARP):
4293 case htons(ETH_P_IP):
4294 case htons(ETH_P_IPV6):
4295 case htons(ETH_P_8021Q):
4296 case htons(ETH_P_8021AD):
4297 return true;
4298 default:
4299 return false;
4300 }
4301}
4302
4303static inline int nf_ingress(struct sk_buff *skb, struct packet_type **pt_prev,
4304 int *ret, struct net_device *orig_dev)
4305{
4306#ifdef CONFIG_NETFILTER_INGRESS
4307 if (nf_hook_ingress_active(skb)) {
4308 int ingress_retval;
4309
4310 if (*pt_prev) {
4311 *ret = deliver_skb(skb, *pt_prev, orig_dev);
4312 *pt_prev = NULL;
4313 }
4314
4315 rcu_read_lock();
4316 ingress_retval = nf_hook_ingress(skb);
4317 rcu_read_unlock();
4318 return ingress_retval;
4319 }
4320#endif /* CONFIG_NETFILTER_INGRESS */
4321 return 0;
4322}
4323
4324static int __netif_receive_skb_core(struct sk_buff *skb, bool pfmemalloc)
4325{
4326 struct packet_type *ptype, *pt_prev;
4327 rx_handler_func_t *rx_handler;
4328 struct net_device *orig_dev;
4329 bool deliver_exact = false;
4330 int ret = NET_RX_DROP;
4331 __be16 type;
4332
4333 net_timestamp_check(!netdev_tstamp_prequeue, skb);
4334
4335 trace_netif_receive_skb(skb);
4336
4337 orig_dev = skb->dev;
4338
4339 skb_reset_network_header(skb);
4340 if (!skb_transport_header_was_set(skb))
4341 skb_reset_transport_header(skb);
4342 skb_reset_mac_len(skb);
4343
4344 pt_prev = NULL;
4345
4346another_round:
4347 skb->skb_iif = skb->dev->ifindex;
4348
4349 __this_cpu_inc(softnet_data.processed);
4350
4351 if (skb->protocol == cpu_to_be16(ETH_P_8021Q) ||
4352 skb->protocol == cpu_to_be16(ETH_P_8021AD)) {
4353 skb = skb_vlan_untag(skb);
4354 if (unlikely(!skb))
4355 goto out;
4356 }
4357
4358 if (skb_skip_tc_classify(skb))
4359 goto skip_classify;
4360
4361 if (pfmemalloc)
4362 goto skip_taps;
4363
4364 list_for_each_entry_rcu(ptype, &ptype_all, list) {
4365 if (pt_prev)
4366 ret = deliver_skb(skb, pt_prev, orig_dev);
4367 pt_prev = ptype;
4368 }
4369
4370 list_for_each_entry_rcu(ptype, &skb->dev->ptype_all, list) {
4371 if (pt_prev)
4372 ret = deliver_skb(skb, pt_prev, orig_dev);
4373 pt_prev = ptype;
4374 }
4375
4376skip_taps:
4377#ifdef CONFIG_NET_INGRESS
4378 if (static_key_false(&ingress_needed)) {
4379 skb = sch_handle_ingress(skb, &pt_prev, &ret, orig_dev);
4380 if (!skb)
4381 goto out;
4382
4383 if (nf_ingress(skb, &pt_prev, &ret, orig_dev) < 0)
4384 goto out;
4385 }
4386#endif
4387 skb_reset_tc(skb);
4388skip_classify:
4389 if (pfmemalloc && !skb_pfmemalloc_protocol(skb))
4390 goto drop;
4391
4392 if (skb_vlan_tag_present(skb)) {
4393 if (pt_prev) {
4394 ret = deliver_skb(skb, pt_prev, orig_dev);
4395 pt_prev = NULL;
4396 }
4397 if (vlan_do_receive(&skb))
4398 goto another_round;
4399 else if (unlikely(!skb))
4400 goto out;
4401 }
4402
4403 rx_handler = rcu_dereference(skb->dev->rx_handler);
4404 if (rx_handler) {
4405 if (pt_prev) {
4406 ret = deliver_skb(skb, pt_prev, orig_dev);
4407 pt_prev = NULL;
4408 }
4409 switch (rx_handler(&skb)) {
4410 case RX_HANDLER_CONSUMED:
4411 ret = NET_RX_SUCCESS;
4412 goto out;
4413 case RX_HANDLER_ANOTHER:
4414 goto another_round;
4415 case RX_HANDLER_EXACT:
4416 deliver_exact = true;
4417 case RX_HANDLER_PASS:
4418 break;
4419 default:
4420 BUG();
4421 }
4422 }
4423
4424 if (unlikely(skb_vlan_tag_present(skb))) {
4425 if (skb_vlan_tag_get_id(skb))
4426 skb->pkt_type = PACKET_OTHERHOST;
4427 /* Note: we might in the future use prio bits
4428 * and set skb->priority like in vlan_do_receive()
4429 * For the time being, just ignore Priority Code Point
4430 */
4431 skb->vlan_tci = 0;
4432 }
4433
4434 type = skb->protocol;
4435
4436 /* deliver only exact match when indicated */
4437 if (likely(!deliver_exact)) {
4438 deliver_ptype_list_skb(skb, &pt_prev, orig_dev, type,
4439 &ptype_base[ntohs(type) &
4440 PTYPE_HASH_MASK]);
4441 }
4442
4443 deliver_ptype_list_skb(skb, &pt_prev, orig_dev, type,
4444 &orig_dev->ptype_specific);
4445
4446 if (unlikely(skb->dev != orig_dev)) {
4447 deliver_ptype_list_skb(skb, &pt_prev, orig_dev, type,
4448 &skb->dev->ptype_specific);
4449 }
4450
4451 if (pt_prev) {
4452 if (unlikely(skb_orphan_frags_rx(skb, GFP_ATOMIC)))
4453 goto drop;
4454 else
4455 ret = pt_prev->func(skb, skb->dev, pt_prev, orig_dev);
4456 } else {
4457drop:
4458 if (!deliver_exact)
4459 atomic_long_inc(&skb->dev->rx_dropped);
4460 else
4461 atomic_long_inc(&skb->dev->rx_nohandler);
4462 kfree_skb(skb);
4463 /* Jamal, now you will not able to escape explaining
4464 * me how you were going to use this. :-)
4465 */
4466 ret = NET_RX_DROP;
4467 }
4468
4469out:
4470 return ret;
4471}
4472
4473static int __netif_receive_skb(struct sk_buff *skb)
4474{
4475 int ret;
4476
4477 if (sk_memalloc_socks() && skb_pfmemalloc(skb)) {
4478 unsigned int noreclaim_flag;
4479
4480 /*
4481 * PFMEMALLOC skbs are special, they should
4482 * - be delivered to SOCK_MEMALLOC sockets only
4483 * - stay away from userspace
4484 * - have bounded memory usage
4485 *
4486 * Use PF_MEMALLOC as this saves us from propagating the allocation
4487 * context down to all allocation sites.
4488 */
4489 noreclaim_flag = memalloc_noreclaim_save();
4490 ret = __netif_receive_skb_core(skb, true);
4491 memalloc_noreclaim_restore(noreclaim_flag);
4492 } else
4493 ret = __netif_receive_skb_core(skb, false);
4494
4495 return ret;
4496}
4497
4498static int generic_xdp_install(struct net_device *dev, struct netdev_xdp *xdp)
4499{
4500 struct bpf_prog *old = rtnl_dereference(dev->xdp_prog);
4501 struct bpf_prog *new = xdp->prog;
4502 int ret = 0;
4503
4504 switch (xdp->command) {
4505 case XDP_SETUP_PROG:
4506 rcu_assign_pointer(dev->xdp_prog, new);
4507 if (old)
4508 bpf_prog_put(old);
4509
4510 if (old && !new) {
4511 static_key_slow_dec(&generic_xdp_needed);
4512 } else if (new && !old) {
4513 static_key_slow_inc(&generic_xdp_needed);
4514 dev_disable_lro(dev);
4515 }
4516 break;
4517
4518 case XDP_QUERY_PROG:
4519 xdp->prog_attached = !!old;
4520 xdp->prog_id = old ? old->aux->id : 0;
4521 break;
4522
4523 default:
4524 ret = -EINVAL;
4525 break;
4526 }
4527
4528 return ret;
4529}
4530
4531static int netif_receive_skb_internal(struct sk_buff *skb)
4532{
4533 int ret;
4534
4535 net_timestamp_check(netdev_tstamp_prequeue, skb);
4536
4537 if (skb_defer_rx_timestamp(skb))
4538 return NET_RX_SUCCESS;
4539
4540 if (static_key_false(&generic_xdp_needed)) {
4541 int ret;
4542
4543 preempt_disable();
4544 rcu_read_lock();
4545 ret = do_xdp_generic(rcu_dereference(skb->dev->xdp_prog), skb);
4546 rcu_read_unlock();
4547 preempt_enable();
4548
4549 if (ret != XDP_PASS)
4550 return NET_RX_DROP;
4551 }
4552
4553 rcu_read_lock();
4554#ifdef CONFIG_RPS
4555 if (static_key_false(&rps_needed)) {
4556 struct rps_dev_flow voidflow, *rflow = &voidflow;
4557 int cpu = get_rps_cpu(skb->dev, skb, &rflow);
4558
4559 if (cpu >= 0) {
4560 ret = enqueue_to_backlog(skb, cpu, &rflow->last_qtail);
4561 rcu_read_unlock();
4562 return ret;
4563 }
4564 }
4565#endif
4566 ret = __netif_receive_skb(skb);
4567 rcu_read_unlock();
4568 return ret;
4569}
4570
4571/**
4572 * netif_receive_skb - process receive buffer from network
4573 * @skb: buffer to process
4574 *
4575 * netif_receive_skb() is the main receive data processing function.
4576 * It always succeeds. The buffer may be dropped during processing
4577 * for congestion control or by the protocol layers.
4578 *
4579 * This function may only be called from softirq context and interrupts
4580 * should be enabled.
4581 *
4582 * Return values (usually ignored):
4583 * NET_RX_SUCCESS: no congestion
4584 * NET_RX_DROP: packet was dropped
4585 */
4586int netif_receive_skb(struct sk_buff *skb)
4587{
4588 trace_netif_receive_skb_entry(skb);
4589
4590 return netif_receive_skb_internal(skb);
4591}
4592EXPORT_SYMBOL(netif_receive_skb);
4593
4594DEFINE_PER_CPU(struct work_struct, flush_works);
4595
4596/* Network device is going away, flush any packets still pending */
4597static void flush_backlog(struct work_struct *work)
4598{
4599 struct sk_buff *skb, *tmp;
4600 struct softnet_data *sd;
4601
4602 local_bh_disable();
4603 sd = this_cpu_ptr(&softnet_data);
4604
4605 local_irq_disable();
4606 rps_lock(sd);
4607 skb_queue_walk_safe(&sd->input_pkt_queue, skb, tmp) {
4608 if (skb->dev->reg_state == NETREG_UNREGISTERING) {
4609 __skb_unlink(skb, &sd->input_pkt_queue);
4610 kfree_skb(skb);
4611 input_queue_head_incr(sd);
4612 }
4613 }
4614 rps_unlock(sd);
4615 local_irq_enable();
4616
4617 skb_queue_walk_safe(&sd->process_queue, skb, tmp) {
4618 if (skb->dev->reg_state == NETREG_UNREGISTERING) {
4619 __skb_unlink(skb, &sd->process_queue);
4620 kfree_skb(skb);
4621 input_queue_head_incr(sd);
4622 }
4623 }
4624 local_bh_enable();
4625}
4626
4627static void flush_all_backlogs(void)
4628{
4629 unsigned int cpu;
4630
4631 get_online_cpus();
4632
4633 for_each_online_cpu(cpu)
4634 queue_work_on(cpu, system_highpri_wq,
4635 per_cpu_ptr(&flush_works, cpu));
4636
4637 for_each_online_cpu(cpu)
4638 flush_work(per_cpu_ptr(&flush_works, cpu));
4639
4640 put_online_cpus();
4641}
4642
4643static int napi_gro_complete(struct sk_buff *skb)
4644{
4645 struct packet_offload *ptype;
4646 __be16 type = skb->protocol;
4647 struct list_head *head = &offload_base;
4648 int err = -ENOENT;
4649
4650 BUILD_BUG_ON(sizeof(struct napi_gro_cb) > sizeof(skb->cb));
4651
4652 if (NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->count == 1) {
4653 skb_shinfo(skb)->gso_size = 0;
4654 goto out;
4655 }
4656
4657 rcu_read_lock();
4658 list_for_each_entry_rcu(ptype, head, list) {
4659 if (ptype->type != type || !ptype->callbacks.gro_complete)
4660 continue;
4661
4662 err = ptype->callbacks.gro_complete(skb, 0);
4663 break;
4664 }
4665 rcu_read_unlock();
4666
4667 if (err) {
4668 WARN_ON(&ptype->list == head);
4669 kfree_skb(skb);
4670 return NET_RX_SUCCESS;
4671 }
4672
4673out:
4674 return netif_receive_skb_internal(skb);
4675}
4676
4677/* napi->gro_list contains packets ordered by age.
4678 * youngest packets at the head of it.
4679 * Complete skbs in reverse order to reduce latencies.
4680 */
4681void napi_gro_flush(struct napi_struct *napi, bool flush_old)
4682{
4683 struct sk_buff *skb, *prev = NULL;
4684
4685 /* scan list and build reverse chain */
4686 for (skb = napi->gro_list; skb != NULL; skb = skb->next) {
4687 skb->prev = prev;
4688 prev = skb;
4689 }
4690
4691 for (skb = prev; skb; skb = prev) {
4692 skb->next = NULL;
4693
4694 if (flush_old && NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->age == jiffies)
4695 return;
4696
4697 prev = skb->prev;
4698 napi_gro_complete(skb);
4699 napi->gro_count--;
4700 }
4701
4702 napi->gro_list = NULL;
4703}
4704EXPORT_SYMBOL(napi_gro_flush);
4705
4706static void gro_list_prepare(struct napi_struct *napi, struct sk_buff *skb)
4707{
4708 struct sk_buff *p;
4709 unsigned int maclen = skb->dev->hard_header_len;
4710 u32 hash = skb_get_hash_raw(skb);
4711
4712 for (p = napi->gro_list; p; p = p->next) {
4713 unsigned long diffs;
4714
4715 NAPI_GRO_CB(p)->flush = 0;
4716
4717 if (hash != skb_get_hash_raw(p)) {
4718 NAPI_GRO_CB(p)->same_flow = 0;
4719 continue;
4720 }
4721
4722 diffs = (unsigned long)p->dev ^ (unsigned long)skb->dev;
4723 diffs |= p->vlan_tci ^ skb->vlan_tci;
4724 diffs |= skb_metadata_dst_cmp(p, skb);
4725 if (maclen == ETH_HLEN)
4726 diffs |= compare_ether_header(skb_mac_header(p),
4727 skb_mac_header(skb));
4728 else if (!diffs)
4729 diffs = memcmp(skb_mac_header(p),
4730 skb_mac_header(skb),
4731 maclen);
4732 NAPI_GRO_CB(p)->same_flow = !diffs;
4733 }
4734}
4735
4736static void skb_gro_reset_offset(struct sk_buff *skb)
4737{
4738 const struct skb_shared_info *pinfo = skb_shinfo(skb);
4739 const skb_frag_t *frag0 = &pinfo->frags[0];
4740
4741 NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->data_offset = 0;
4742 NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->frag0 = NULL;
4743 NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->frag0_len = 0;
4744
4745 if (skb_mac_header(skb) == skb_tail_pointer(skb) &&
4746 pinfo->nr_frags &&
4747 !PageHighMem(skb_frag_page(frag0))) {
4748 NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->frag0 = skb_frag_address(frag0);
4749 NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->frag0_len = min_t(unsigned int,
4750 skb_frag_size(frag0),
4751 skb->end - skb->tail);
4752 }
4753}
4754
4755static void gro_pull_from_frag0(struct sk_buff *skb, int grow)
4756{
4757 struct skb_shared_info *pinfo = skb_shinfo(skb);
4758
4759 BUG_ON(skb->end - skb->tail < grow);
4760
4761 memcpy(skb_tail_pointer(skb), NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->frag0, grow);
4762
4763 skb->data_len -= grow;
4764 skb->tail += grow;
4765
4766 pinfo->frags[0].page_offset += grow;
4767 skb_frag_size_sub(&pinfo->frags[0], grow);
4768
4769 if (unlikely(!skb_frag_size(&pinfo->frags[0]))) {
4770 skb_frag_unref(skb, 0);
4771 memmove(pinfo->frags, pinfo->frags + 1,
4772 --pinfo->nr_frags * sizeof(pinfo->frags[0]));
4773 }
4774}
4775
4776static enum gro_result dev_gro_receive(struct napi_struct *napi, struct sk_buff *skb)
4777{
4778 struct sk_buff **pp = NULL;
4779 struct packet_offload *ptype;
4780 __be16 type = skb->protocol;
4781 struct list_head *head = &offload_base;
4782 int same_flow;
4783 enum gro_result ret;
4784 int grow;
4785
4786 if (netif_elide_gro(skb->dev))
4787 goto normal;
4788
4789 gro_list_prepare(napi, skb);
4790
4791 rcu_read_lock();
4792 list_for_each_entry_rcu(ptype, head, list) {
4793 if (ptype->type != type || !ptype->callbacks.gro_receive)
4794 continue;
4795
4796 skb_set_network_header(skb, skb_gro_offset(skb));
4797 skb_reset_mac_len(skb);
4798 NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->same_flow = 0;
4799 NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->flush = skb_is_gso(skb) || skb_has_frag_list(skb);
4800 NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->free = 0;
4801 NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->encap_mark = 0;
4802 NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->recursion_counter = 0;
4803 NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->is_fou = 0;
4804 NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->is_atomic = 1;
4805 NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->gro_remcsum_start = 0;
4806
4807 /* Setup for GRO checksum validation */
4808 switch (skb->ip_summed) {
4809 case CHECKSUM_COMPLETE:
4810 NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->csum = skb->csum;
4811 NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->csum_valid = 1;
4812 NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->csum_cnt = 0;
4813 break;
4814 case CHECKSUM_UNNECESSARY:
4815 NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->csum_cnt = skb->csum_level + 1;
4816 NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->csum_valid = 0;
4817 break;
4818 default:
4819 NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->csum_cnt = 0;
4820 NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->csum_valid = 0;
4821 }
4822
4823 pp = ptype->callbacks.gro_receive(&napi->gro_list, skb);
4824 break;
4825 }
4826 rcu_read_unlock();
4827
4828 if (&ptype->list == head)
4829 goto normal;
4830
4831 if (IS_ERR(pp) && PTR_ERR(pp) == -EINPROGRESS) {
4832 ret = GRO_CONSUMED;
4833 goto ok;
4834 }
4835
4836 same_flow = NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->same_flow;
4837 ret = NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->free ? GRO_MERGED_FREE : GRO_MERGED;
4838
4839 if (pp) {
4840 struct sk_buff *nskb = *pp;
4841
4842 *pp = nskb->next;
4843 nskb->next = NULL;
4844 napi_gro_complete(nskb);
4845 napi->gro_count--;
4846 }
4847
4848 if (same_flow)
4849 goto ok;
4850
4851 if (NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->flush)
4852 goto normal;
4853
4854 if (unlikely(napi->gro_count >= MAX_GRO_SKBS)) {
4855 struct sk_buff *nskb = napi->gro_list;
4856
4857 /* locate the end of the list to select the 'oldest' flow */
4858 while (nskb->next) {
4859 pp = &nskb->next;
4860 nskb = *pp;
4861 }
4862 *pp = NULL;
4863 nskb->next = NULL;
4864 napi_gro_complete(nskb);
4865 } else {
4866 napi->gro_count++;
4867 }
4868 NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->count = 1;
4869 NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->age = jiffies;
4870 NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->last = skb;
4871 skb_shinfo(skb)->gso_size = skb_gro_len(skb);
4872 skb->next = napi->gro_list;
4873 napi->gro_list = skb;
4874 ret = GRO_HELD;
4875
4876pull:
4877 grow = skb_gro_offset(skb) - skb_headlen(skb);
4878 if (grow > 0)
4879 gro_pull_from_frag0(skb, grow);
4880ok:
4881 return ret;
4882
4883normal:
4884 ret = GRO_NORMAL;
4885 goto pull;
4886}
4887
4888struct packet_offload *gro_find_receive_by_type(__be16 type)
4889{
4890 struct list_head *offload_head = &offload_base;
4891 struct packet_offload *ptype;
4892
4893 list_for_each_entry_rcu(ptype, offload_head, list) {
4894 if (ptype->type != type || !ptype->callbacks.gro_receive)
4895 continue;
4896 return ptype;
4897 }
4898 return NULL;
4899}
4900EXPORT_SYMBOL(gro_find_receive_by_type);

4906
4907 list_for_each_entry_rcu(ptype, offload_head, list) {
4908 if (ptype->type != type || !ptype->callbacks.gro_complete)

4916static void napi_skb_free_stolen_head(struct sk_buff *skb)
4917{
4918 skb_dst_drop(skb);
4919 secpath_reset(skb);
4920 kmem_cache_free(skbuff_head_cache, skb);
4921}
4922
4923static gro_result_t napi_skb_finish(gro_result_t ret, struct sk_buff *skb)
4924{
4925 switch (ret) {
4926 case GRO_NORMAL:
4927 if (netif_receive_skb_internal(skb))
4928 ret = GRO_DROP;
4929 break;
4930
4931 case GRO_DROP:
4932 kfree_skb(skb);
4933 break;
4934
4935 case GRO_MERGED_FREE:
4936 if (NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->free == NAPI_GRO_FREE_STOLEN_HEAD)
4937 napi_skb_free_stolen_head(skb);
4938 else
4939 __kfree_skb(skb);
4940 break;
4941
4942 case GRO_HELD:
4943 case GRO_MERGED:
4944 case GRO_CONSUMED:
4945 break;
4946 }
4947
4948 return ret;
4949}
4950
4951gro_result_t napi_gro_receive(struct napi_struct *napi, struct sk_buff *skb)
4952{
4953 skb_mark_napi_id(skb, napi);
4954 trace_napi_gro_receive_entry(skb);
4955
4956 skb_gro_reset_offset(skb);
4957
4958 return napi_skb_finish(dev_gro_receive(napi, skb), skb);
4959}
4960EXPORT_SYMBOL(napi_gro_receive);
4961
4962static void napi_reuse_skb(struct napi_struct *napi, struct sk_buff *skb)
4963{
4964 if (unlikely(skb->pfmemalloc)) {
4965 consume_skb(skb);
4966 return;
4967 }
4968 __skb_pull(skb, skb_headlen(skb));
4969 /* restore the reserve we had after netdev_alloc_skb_ip_align() */
4970 skb_reserve(skb, NET_SKB_PAD + NET_IP_ALIGN - skb_headroom(skb));
4971 skb->vlan_tci = 0;
4972 skb->dev = napi->dev;
4973 skb->skb_iif = 0;
4974 skb->encapsulation = 0;
4975 skb_shinfo(skb)->gso_type = 0;
4976 skb->truesize = SKB_TRUESIZE(skb_end_offset(skb));
4977 secpath_reset(skb);
4978
4979 napi->skb = skb;
4980}
4981
4982struct sk_buff *napi_get_frags(struct napi_struct *napi)
4983{
4984 struct sk_buff *skb = napi->skb;
4985
4986 if (!skb) {
4987 skb = napi_alloc_skb(napi, GRO_MAX_HEAD);
4988 if (skb) {
4989 napi->skb = skb;
4990 skb_mark_napi_id(skb, napi);
4991 }
4992 }
4993 return skb;
4994}
4995EXPORT_SYMBOL(napi_get_frags);
4996
4997static gro_result_t napi_frags_finish(struct napi_struct *napi,
4998 struct sk_buff *skb,
4999 gro_result_t ret)
5000{
5001 switch (ret) {
5002 case GRO_NORMAL:
5003 case GRO_HELD:
5004 __skb_push(skb, ETH_HLEN);
5005 skb->protocol = eth_type_trans(skb, skb->dev);
5006 if (ret == GRO_NORMAL && netif_receive_skb_internal(skb))
5007 ret = GRO_DROP;
5008 break;
5009
5010 case GRO_DROP:
5011 napi_reuse_skb(napi, skb);
5012 break;
5013
5014 case GRO_MERGED_FREE:
5015 if (NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->free == NAPI_GRO_FREE_STOLEN_HEAD)
5016 napi_skb_free_stolen_head(skb);
5017 else
5018 napi_reuse_skb(napi, skb);
5019 break;
5020
5021 case GRO_MERGED:
5022 case GRO_CONSUMED:
5023 break;
5024 }
5025
5026 return ret;
5027}
5028
5029/* Upper GRO stack assumes network header starts at gro_offset=0
5030 * Drivers could call both napi_gro_frags() and napi_gro_receive()
5031 * We copy ethernet header into skb->data to have a common layout.
5032 */
5033static struct sk_buff *napi_frags_skb(struct napi_struct *napi)
5034{
5035 struct sk_buff *skb = napi->skb;
5036 const struct ethhdr *eth;
5037 unsigned int hlen = sizeof(*eth);
5038
5039 napi->skb = NULL;
5040
5041 skb_reset_mac_header(skb);
5042 skb_gro_reset_offset(skb);
5043
5044 eth = skb_gro_header_fast(skb, 0);
5045 if (unlikely(skb_gro_header_hard(skb, hlen))) {
5046 eth = skb_gro_header_slow(skb, hlen, 0);
5047 if (unlikely(!eth)) {
5048 net_warn_ratelimited("%s: dropping impossible skb from %s\n",
5049 __func__, napi->dev->name);
5050 napi_reuse_skb(napi, skb);
5051 return NULL;
5052 }
5053 } else {
5054 gro_pull_from_frag0(skb, hlen);
5055 NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->frag0 += hlen;
5056 NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->frag0_len -= hlen;
5057 }
5058 __skb_pull(skb, hlen);
5059
5060 /*
5061 * This works because the only protocols we care about don't require
5062 * special handling.
5063 * We'll fix it up properly in napi_frags_finish()
5064 */
5065 skb->protocol = eth->h_proto;
5066
5067 return skb;
5068}
5069
5070gro_result_t napi_gro_frags(struct napi_struct *napi)
5071{
5072 struct sk_buff *skb = napi_frags_skb(napi);
5073
5074 if (!skb)
5075 return GRO_DROP;
5076
5077 trace_napi_gro_frags_entry(skb);
5078
5079 return napi_frags_finish(napi, skb, dev_gro_receive(napi, skb));
5080}
5081EXPORT_SYMBOL(napi_gro_frags);
5082
5083/* Compute the checksum from gro_offset and return the folded value
5084 * after adding in any pseudo checksum.
5085 */
5086__sum16 __skb_gro_checksum_complete(struct sk_buff *skb)
5087{
5088 __wsum wsum;
5089 __sum16 sum;
5090
5091 wsum = skb_checksum(skb, skb_gro_offset(skb), skb_gro_len(skb), 0);
5092
5093 /* NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->csum holds pseudo checksum */
5094 sum = csum_fold(csum_add(NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->csum, wsum));
5095 if (likely(!sum)) {
5096 if (unlikely(skb->ip_summed == CHECKSUM_COMPLETE) &&
5097 !skb->csum_complete_sw)
5098 netdev_rx_csum_fault(skb->dev);
5099 }
5100
5101 NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->csum = wsum;
5102 NAPI_GRO_CB(skb)->csum_valid = 1;
5103
5104 return sum;
5105}
5106EXPORT_SYMBOL(__skb_gro_checksum_complete);

5108static void net_rps_send_ipi(struct softnet_data *remsd)
5109{
5110#ifdef CONFIG_RPS
5111 while (remsd) {
5112 struct softnet_data *next = remsd->rps_ipi_next;
5113
5114 if (cpu_online(remsd->cpu))
5115 smp_call_function_single_async(remsd->cpu, &remsd->csd);
5116 remsd = next;
5117 }
5118#endif
5119}
5120
5121/*
5122 * net_rps_action_and_irq_enable sends any pending IPI's for rps.
5123 * Note: called with local irq disabled, but exits with local irq enabled.
5124 */
5125static void net_rps_action_and_irq_enable(struct softnet_data *sd)
5126{
5127#ifdef CONFIG_RPS
5128 struct softnet_data *remsd = sd->rps_ipi_list;
5129
5130 if (remsd) {
5131 sd->rps_ipi_list = NULL;
5132
5133 local_irq_enable();
5134
5135 /* Send pending IPI's to kick RPS processing on remote cpus. */
5136 net_rps_send_ipi(remsd);
5137 } else
5138#endif
5139 local_irq_enable();
5140}
5141
5142static bool sd_has_rps_ipi_waiting(struct softnet_data *sd)
5143{
5144#ifdef CONFIG_RPS
5145 return sd->rps_ipi_list != NULL;
5146#else
5147 return false;
5148#endif
5149}
5150
5151static int process_backlog(struct napi_struct *napi, int quota)
5152{
5153 struct softnet_data *sd = container_of(napi, struct softnet_data, backlog);
5154 bool again = true;
5155 int work = 0;
5156
5157 /* Check if we have pending ipi, its better to send them now,
5158 * not waiting net_rx_action() end.
5159 */
5160 if (sd_has_rps_ipi_waiting(sd)) {
5161 local_irq_disable();
5162 net_rps_action_and_irq_enable(sd);
5163 }
5164
5165 napi->weight = dev_rx_weight;
5166 while (again) {
5167 struct sk_buff *skb;
5168
5169 while ((skb = __skb_dequeue(&sd->process_queue))) {
5170 rcu_read_lock();
5171 __netif_receive_skb(skb);
5172 rcu_read_unlock();
5173 input_queue_head_incr(sd);
5174 if (++work >= quota)
5175 return work;
5176
5177 }
5178
5179 local_irq_disable();
5180 rps_lock(sd);
5181 if (skb_queue_empty(&sd->input_pkt_queue)) {
5182 /*
5183 * Inline a custom version of __napi_complete().
5184 * only current cpu owns and manipulates this napi,
5185 * and NAPI_STATE_SCHED is the only possible flag set
5186 * on backlog.
5187 * We can use a plain write instead of clear_bit(),
5188 * and we dont need an smp_mb() memory barrier.
5189 */
5190 napi->state = 0;
5191 again = false;
5192 } else {
5193 skb_queue_splice_tail_init(&sd->input_pkt_queue,
5194 &sd->process_queue);
5195 }
5196 rps_unlock(sd);
5197 local_irq_enable();
5198 }
5199
5200 return work;
5201}
5202
5203/**
5204 * __napi_schedule - schedule for receive
5205 * @n: entry to schedule
5206 *
5207 * The entry's receive function will be scheduled to run.
5208 * Consider using __napi_schedule_irqoff() if hard irqs are masked.
5209 */
5210void __napi_schedule(struct napi_struct *n)
5211{
5212 unsigned long flags;
5213
5214 local_irq_save(flags);
5215 ____napi_schedule(this_cpu_ptr(&softnet_data), n);
5216 local_irq_restore(flags);
5217}
5218EXPORT_SYMBOL(__napi_schedule);
5219
5220/**
5221 * napi_schedule_prep - check if napi can be scheduled
5222 * @n: napi context
5223 *
5224 * Test if NAPI routine is already running, and if not mark
5225 * it as running. This is used as a condition variable
5226 * insure only one NAPI poll instance runs. We also make
5227 * sure there is no pending NAPI disable.
5228 */
5229bool napi_schedule_prep(struct napi_struct *n)
5230{
5231 unsigned long val, new;
5232
5233 do {
5234 val = READ_ONCE(n->state);
5235 if (unlikely(val & NAPIF_STATE_DISABLE))
5236 return false;
5237 new = val | NAPIF_STATE_SCHED;
5238
5239 /* Sets STATE_MISSED bit if STATE_SCHED was already set
5240 * This was suggested by Alexander Duyck, as compiler
5241 * emits better code than :
5242 * if (val & NAPIF_STATE_SCHED)
5243 * new |= NAPIF_STATE_MISSED;
5244 */
5245 new |= (val & NAPIF_STATE_SCHED) / NAPIF_STATE_SCHED *
5246 NAPIF_STATE_MISSED;
5247 } while (cmpxchg(&n->state, val, new) != val);
5248
5249 return !(val & NAPIF_STATE_SCHED);
5250}
5251EXPORT_SYMBOL(napi_schedule_prep);
5252
5253/**
5254 * __napi_schedule_irqoff - schedule for receive
5255 * @n: entry to schedule
5256 *
5257 * Variant of __napi_schedule() assuming hard irqs are masked
5258 */
5259void __napi_schedule_irqoff(struct napi_struct *n)
5260{
5261 ____napi_schedule(this_cpu_ptr(&softnet_data), n);
5262}
5263EXPORT_SYMBOL(__napi_schedule_irqoff);
5264
5265bool napi_complete_done(struct napi_struct *n, int work_done)
5266{
5267 unsigned long flags, val, new;
5268
5269 /*
5270 * 1) Don't let napi dequeue from the cpu poll list
5271 * just in case its running on a different cpu.
5272 * 2) If we are busy polling, do nothing here, we have
5273 * the guarantee we will be called later.
5274 */
5275 if (unlikely(n->state & (NAPIF_STATE_NPSVC |
5276 NAPIF_STATE_IN_BUSY_POLL)))
5277 return false;
5278
5279 if (n->gro_list) {
5280 unsigned long timeout = 0;
5281
5282 if (work_done)
5283 timeout = n->dev->gro_flush_timeout;
5284
5285 if (timeout)
5286 hrtimer_start(&n->timer, ns_to_ktime(timeout),
5287 HRTIMER_MODE_REL_PINNED);
5288 else
5289 napi_gro_flush(n, false);
5290 }
5291 if (unlikely(!list_empty(&n->poll_list))) {
5292 /* If n->poll_list is not empty, we need to mask irqs */
5293 local_irq_save(flags);
5294 list_del_init(&n->poll_list);
5295 local_irq_restore(flags);
5296 }
5297
5298 do {
5299 val = READ_ONCE(n->state);
5300
5301 WARN_ON_ONCE(!(val & NAPIF_STATE_SCHED));
5302
5303 new = val & ~(NAPIF_STATE_MISSED | NAPIF_STATE_SCHED);
5304
5305 /* If STATE_MISSED was set, leave STATE_SCHED set,
5306 * because we will call napi->poll() one more time.
5307 * This C code was suggested by Alexander Duyck to help gcc.
5308 */
5309 new |= (val & NAPIF_STATE_MISSED) / NAPIF_STATE_MISSED *
5310 NAPIF_STATE_SCHED;
5311 } while (cmpxchg(&n->state, val, new) != val);
5312
5313 if (unlikely(val & NAPIF_STATE_MISSED)) {
5314 __napi_schedule(n);
5315 return false;
5316 }
5317
5318 return true;
5319}
5320EXPORT_SYMBOL(napi_complete_done);
5321
5322/* must be called under rcu_read_lock(), as we dont take a reference */
5323static struct napi_struct *napi_by_id(unsigned int napi_id)
5324{
5325 unsigned int hash = napi_id % HASH_SIZE(napi_hash);
5326 struct napi_struct *napi;
5327
5328 hlist_for_each_entry_rcu(napi, &napi_hash[hash], napi_hash_node)
5329 if (napi->napi_id == napi_id)
5330 return napi;
5331
5332 return NULL;
5333}
5334
5335#if defined(CONFIG_NET_RX_BUSY_POLL)
5336
5337#define BUSY_POLL_BUDGET 8
5338
5339static void busy_poll_stop(struct napi_struct *napi, void *have_poll_lock)
5340{
5341 int rc;
5342
5343 /* Busy polling means there is a high chance device driver hard irq
5344 * could not grab NAPI_STATE_SCHED, and that NAPI_STATE_MISSED was
5345 * set in napi_schedule_prep().
5346 * Since we are about to call napi->poll() once more, we can safely
5347 * clear NAPI_STATE_MISSED.
5348 *
5349 * Note: x86 could use a single "lock and ..." instruction
5350 * to perform these two clear_bit()
5351 */
5352 clear_bit(NAPI_STATE_MISSED, &napi->state);
5353 clear_bit(NAPI_STATE_IN_BUSY_POLL, &napi->state);
5354
5355 local_bh_disable();
5356
5357 /* All we really want here is to re-enable device interrupts.
5358 * Ideally, a new ndo_busy_poll_stop() could avoid another round.
5359 */
5360 rc = napi->poll(napi, BUSY_POLL_BUDGET);
5361 trace_napi_poll(napi, rc, BUSY_POLL_BUDGET);
5362 netpoll_poll_unlock(have_poll_lock);
5363 if (rc == BUSY_POLL_BUDGET)
5364 __napi_schedule(napi);
5365 local_bh_enable();
5366}
5367
5368void napi_busy_loop(unsigned int napi_id,
5369 bool (*loop_end)(void *, unsigned long),
5370 void *loop_end_arg)
5371{
5372 unsigned long start_time = loop_end ? busy_loop_current_time() : 0;
5373 int (*napi_poll)(struct napi_struct *napi, int budget);
5374 void *have_poll_lock = NULL;
5375 struct napi_struct *napi;
5376
5377restart:
5378 napi_poll = NULL;
5379
5380 rcu_read_lock();
5381
5382 napi = napi_by_id(napi_id);
5383 if (!napi)
5384 goto out;
5385
5386 preempt_disable();
5387 for (;;) {
5388 int work = 0;
5389
5390 local_bh_disable();
5391 if (!napi_poll) {
5392 unsigned long val = READ_ONCE(napi->state);
5393
5394 /* If multiple threads are competing for this napi,
5395 * we avoid dirtying napi->state as much as we can.
5396 */
5397 if (val & (NAPIF_STATE_DISABLE | NAPIF_STATE_SCHED |
5398 NAPIF_STATE_IN_BUSY_POLL))
5399 goto count;
5400 if (cmpxchg(&napi->state, val,
5401 val | NAPIF_STATE_IN_BUSY_POLL |
5402 NAPIF_STATE_SCHED) != val)
5403 goto count;
5404 have_poll_lock = netpoll_poll_lock(napi);
5405 napi_poll = napi->poll;
5406 }
5407 work = napi_poll(napi, BUSY_POLL_BUDGET);
5408 trace_napi_poll(napi, work, BUSY_POLL_BUDGET);
5409count:
5410 if (work > 0)
5411 __NET_ADD_STATS(dev_net(napi->dev),
5412 LINUX_MIB_BUSYPOLLRXPACKETS, work);
5413 local_bh_enable();
5414
5415 if (!loop_end || loop_end(loop_end_arg, start_time))
5416 break;
5417
5418 if (unlikely(need_resched())) {
5419 if (napi_poll)
5420 busy_poll_stop(napi, have_poll_lock);
5421 preempt_enable();
5422 rcu_read_unlock();
5423 cond_resched();
5424 if (loop_end(loop_end_arg, start_time))
5425 return;
5426 goto restart;
5427 }
5428 cpu_relax();
5429 }
5430 if (napi_poll)
5431 busy_poll_stop(napi, have_poll_lock);
5432 preempt_enable();
5433out:
5434 rcu_read_unlock();
5435}
5436EXPORT_SYMBOL(napi_busy_loop);
5437
5438#endif /* CONFIG_NET_RX_BUSY_POLL */
5439
5440static void napi_hash_add(struct napi_struct *napi)
5441{
5442 if (test_bit(NAPI_STATE_NO_BUSY_POLL, &napi->state) ||
5443 test_and_set_bit(NAPI_STATE_HASHED, &napi->state))
5444 return;
5445
5446 spin_lock(&napi_hash_lock);
5447
5448 /* 0..NR_CPUS range is reserved for sender_cpu use */
5449 do {
5450 if (unlikely(++napi_gen_id < MIN_NAPI_ID))
5451 napi_gen_id = MIN_NAPI_ID;
5452 } while (napi_by_id(napi_gen_id));
5453 napi->napi_id = napi_gen_id;
5454
5455 hlist_add_head_rcu(&napi->napi_hash_node,
5456 &napi_hash[napi->napi_id % HASH_SIZE(napi_hash)]);
5457
5458 spin_unlock(&napi_hash_lock);
5459}
5460
5461/* Warning : caller is responsible to make sure rcu grace period
5462 * is respected before freeing memory containing @napi
5463 */
5464bool napi_hash_del(struct napi_struct *napi)
5465{
5466 bool rcu_sync_needed = false;
5467
5468 spin_lock(&napi_hash_lock);
5469
5470 if (test_and_clear_bit(NAPI_STATE_HASHED, &napi->state)) {
5471 rcu_sync_needed = true;
5472 hlist_del_rcu(&napi->napi_hash_node);
5473 }
5474 spin_unlock(&napi_hash_lock);
5475 return rcu_sync_needed;
5476}
5477EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(napi_hash_del);
5478
5479static enum hrtimer_restart napi_watchdog(struct hrtimer *timer)
5480{
5481 struct napi_struct *napi;
5482
5483 napi = container_of(timer, struct napi_struct, timer);
5484
5485 /* Note : we use a relaxed variant of napi_schedule_prep() not setting
5486 * NAPI_STATE_MISSED, since we do not react to a device IRQ.
5487 */
5488 if (napi->gro_list && !napi_disable_pending(napi) &&
5489 !test_and_set_bit(NAPI_STATE_SCHED, &napi->state))
5490 __napi_schedule_irqoff(napi);
5491
5492 return HRTIMER_NORESTART;
5493}
5494
5495void netif_napi_add(struct net_device *dev, struct napi_struct *napi,
5496 int (*poll)(struct napi_struct *, int), int weight)
5497{
5498 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&napi->poll_list);
5499 hrtimer_init(&napi->timer, CLOCK_MONOTONIC, HRTIMER_MODE_REL_PINNED);
5500 napi->timer.function = napi_watchdog;
5501 napi->gro_count = 0;
5502 napi->gro_list = NULL;
5503 napi->skb = NULL;
5504 napi->poll = poll;
5505 if (weight > NAPI_POLL_WEIGHT)
5506 pr_err_once("netif_napi_add() called with weight %d on device %s\n",
5507 weight, dev->name);
5508 napi->weight = weight;
5509 list_add(&napi->dev_list, &dev->napi_list);
5510 napi->dev = dev;
5511#ifdef CONFIG_NETPOLL
5512 napi->poll_owner = -1;
5513#endif
5514 set_bit(NAPI_STATE_SCHED, &napi->state);
5515 napi_hash_add(napi);
5516}
5517EXPORT_SYMBOL(netif_napi_add);
5518
5519void napi_disable(struct napi_struct *n)
5520{
5521 might_sleep();
5522 set_bit(NAPI_STATE_DISABLE, &n->state);
5523
5524 while (test_and_set_bit(NAPI_STATE_SCHED, &n->state))
5525 msleep(1);
5526 while (test_and_set_bit(NAPI_STATE_NPSVC, &n->state))
5527 msleep(1);
5528
5529 hrtimer_cancel(&n->timer);
5530
5531 clear_bit(NAPI_STATE_DISABLE, &n->state);
5532}
5533EXPORT_SYMBOL(napi_disable);
5534
5535/* Must be called in process context */
5536void netif_napi_del(struct napi_struct *napi)
5537{
5538 might_sleep();
5539 if (napi_hash_del(napi))
5540 synchronize_net();
5541 list_del_init(&napi->dev_list);
5542 napi_free_frags(napi);
5543
5544 kfree_skb_list(napi->gro_list);
5545 napi->gro_list = NULL;
5546 napi->gro_count = 0;
5547}
5548EXPORT_SYMBOL(netif_napi_del);
5549
5550static int napi_poll(struct napi_struct *n, struct list_head *repoll)
5551{
5552 void *have;
5553 int work, weight;
5554
5555 list_del_init(&n->poll_list);
5556
5557 have = netpoll_poll_lock(n);
5558
5559 weight = n->weight;
5560
5561 /* This NAPI_STATE_SCHED test is for avoiding a race
5562 * with netpoll's poll_napi(). Only the entity which
5563 * obtains the lock and sees NAPI_STATE_SCHED set will
5564 * actually make the ->poll() call. Therefore we avoid
5565 * accidentally calling ->poll() when NAPI is not scheduled.
5566 */
5567 work = 0;
5568 if (test_bit(NAPI_STATE_SCHED, &n->state)) {
5569 work = n->poll(n, weight);
5570 trace_napi_poll(n, work, weight);
5571 }
5572
5573 WARN_ON_ONCE(work > weight);
5574
5575 if (likely(work < weight))
5576 goto out_unlock;
5577
5578 /* Drivers must not modify the NAPI state if they
5579 * consume the entire weight. In such cases this code
5580 * still "owns" the NAPI instance and therefore can
5581 * move the instance around on the list at-will.
5582 */
5583 if (unlikely(napi_disable_pending(n))) {
5584 napi_complete(n);
5585 goto out_unlock;
5586 }
5587
5588 if (n->gro_list) {
5589 /* flush too old packets
5590 * If HZ < 1000, flush all packets.
5591 */
5592 napi_gro_flush(n, HZ >= 1000);
5593 }
5594
5595 /* Some drivers may have called napi_schedule
5596 * prior to exhausting their budget.
5597 */
5598 if (unlikely(!list_empty(&n->poll_list))) {
5599 pr_warn_once("%s: Budget exhausted after napi rescheduled\n",
5600 n->dev ? n->dev->name : "backlog");
5601 goto out_unlock;
5602 }
5603
5604 list_add_tail(&n->poll_list, repoll);
5605
5606out_unlock:
5607 netpoll_poll_unlock(have);
5608
5609 return work;
5610}
5611
5612static __latent_entropy void net_rx_action(struct softirq_action *h)
5613{
5614 struct softnet_data *sd = this_cpu_ptr(&softnet_data);
5615 unsigned long time_limit = jiffies +
5616 usecs_to_jiffies(netdev_budget_usecs);
5617 int budget = netdev_budget;
5618 LIST_HEAD(list);
5619 LIST_HEAD(repoll);
5620
5621 local_irq_disable();
5622 list_splice_init(&sd->poll_list, &list);
5623 local_irq_enable();
5624
5625 for (;;) {
5626 struct napi_struct *n;
5627
5628 if (list_empty(&list)) {
5629 if (!sd_has_rps_ipi_waiting(sd) && list_empty(&repoll))
5630 goto out;
5631 break;
5632 }
5633
5634 n = list_first_entry(&list, struct napi_struct, poll_list);
5635 budget -= napi_poll(n, &repoll);
5636
5637 /* If softirq window is exhausted then punt.
5638 * Allow this to run for 2 jiffies since which will allow
5639 * an average latency of 1.5/HZ.
5640 */
5641 if (unlikely(budget <= 0 ||
5642 time_after_eq(jiffies, time_limit))) {
5643 sd->time_squeeze++;
5644 break;
5645 }
5646 }
5647
5648 local_irq_disable();
5649
5650 list_splice_tail_init(&sd->poll_list, &list);
5651 list_splice_tail(&repoll, &list);
5652 list_splice(&list, &sd->poll_list);
5653 if (!list_empty(&sd->poll_list))
5654 __raise_softirq_irqoff(NET_RX_SOFTIRQ);
5655
5656 net_rps_action_and_irq_enable(sd);
5657out:
5658 __kfree_skb_flush();
5659}
5660
5661struct netdev_adjacent {
5662 struct net_device *dev;
5663
5664 /* upper master flag, there can only be one master device per list */
5665 bool master;
5666
5667 /* counter for the number of times this device was added to us */
5668 u16 ref_nr;
5669
5670 /* private field for the users */
5671 void *private;
5672
5673 struct list_head list;
5674 struct rcu_head rcu;
5675};
5676
5677static struct netdev_adjacent *__netdev_find_adj(struct net_device *adj_dev,
5678 struct list_head *adj_list)
5679{
5680 struct netdev_adjacent *adj;
5681
5682 list_for_each_entry(adj, adj_list, list) {
5683 if (adj->dev == adj_dev)
5684 return adj;
5685 }
5686 return NULL;
5687}
5688
5689static int __netdev_has_upper_dev(struct net_device *upper_dev, void *data)
5690{
5691 struct net_device *dev = data;
5692
5693 return upper_dev == dev;
5694}
5695
5696/**
5697 * netdev_has_upper_dev - Check if device is linked to an upper device
5698 * @dev: device
5699 * @upper_dev: upper device to check
5700 *
5701 * Find out if a device is linked to specified upper device and return true
5702 * in case it is. Note that this checks only immediate upper device,
5703 * not through a complete stack of devices. The caller must hold the RTNL lock.
5704 */
5705bool netdev_has_upper_dev(struct net_device *dev,
5706 struct net_device *upper_dev)
5707{
5708 ASSERT_RTNL();
5709
5710 return netdev_walk_all_upper_dev_rcu(dev, __netdev_has_upper_dev,
5711 upper_dev);
5712}
5713EXPORT_SYMBOL(netdev_has_upper_dev);
5714
5715/**
5716 * netdev_has_upper_dev_all - Check if device is linked to an upper device
5717 * @dev: device
5718 * @upper_dev: upper device to check
5719 *
5720 * Find out if a device is linked to specified upper device and return true
5721 * in case it is. Note that this checks the entire upper device chain.
5722 * The caller must hold rcu lock.
5723 */
5724
5725bool netdev_has_upper_dev_all_rcu(struct net_device *dev,
5726 struct net_device *upper_dev)
5727{
5728 return !!netdev_walk_all_upper_dev_rcu(dev, __netdev_has_upper_dev,
5729 upper_dev);
5730}
5731EXPORT_SYMBOL(netdev_has_upper_dev_all_rcu);
5732
5733/**
5734 * netdev_has_any_upper_dev - Check if device is linked to some device
5735 * @dev: device
5736 *
5737 * Find out if a device is linked to an upper device and return true in case
5738 * it is. The caller must hold the RTNL lock.
5739 */
5740bool netdev_has_any_upper_dev(struct net_device *dev)
5741{
5742 ASSERT_RTNL();
5743
5744 return !list_empty(&dev->adj_list.upper);
5745}
5746EXPORT_SYMBOL(netdev_has_any_upper_dev);
5747
5748/**
5749 * netdev_master_upper_dev_get - Get master upper device
5750 * @dev: device
5751 *
5752 * Find a master upper device and return pointer to it or NULL in case
5753 * it's not there. The caller must hold the RTNL lock.
5754 */
5755struct net_device *netdev_master_upper_dev_get(struct net_device *dev)
5756{
5757 struct netdev_adjacent *upper;
5758
5759 ASSERT_RTNL();
5760
5761 if (list_empty(&dev->adj_list.upper))
5762 return NULL;
5763
5764 upper = list_first_entry(&dev->adj_list.upper,
5765 struct netdev_adjacent, list);
5766 if (likely(upper->master))
5767 return upper->dev;
5768 return NULL;
5769}
5770EXPORT_SYMBOL(netdev_master_upper_dev_get);
5771
5772/**
5773 * netdev_has_any_lower_dev - Check if device is linked to some device
5774 * @dev: device
5775 *
5776 * Find out if a device is linked to a lower device and return true in case
5777 * it is. The caller must hold the RTNL lock.
5778 */
5779static bool netdev_has_any_lower_dev(struct net_device *dev)
5780{
5781 ASSERT_RTNL();
5782
5783 return !list_empty(&dev->adj_list.lower);
5784}

5786void *netdev_adjacent_get_private(struct list_head *adj_list)
5787{
5788 struct netdev_adjacent *adj;
5789
5790 adj = list_entry(adj_list, struct netdev_adjacent, list);
5791
5792 return adj->private;
5793}
5794EXPORT_SYMBOL(netdev_adjacent_get_private);
5795
5796/**
5797 * netdev_upper_get_next_dev_rcu - Get the next dev from upper list
5798 * @dev: device
5799 * @iter: list_head ** of the current position
5800 *
5801 * Gets the next device from the dev's upper list, starting from iter
5802 * position. The caller must hold RCU read lock.
5803 */
5804struct net_device *netdev_upper_get_next_dev_rcu(struct net_device *dev,
5805 struct list_head **iter)
5806{
5807 struct netdev_adjacent *upper;
5808
5809 WARN_ON_ONCE(!rcu_read_lock_held() && !lockdep_rtnl_is_held());
5810
5811 upper = list_entry_rcu((*iter)->next, struct netdev_adjacent, list);
5812
5813 if (&upper->list == &dev->adj_list.upper)
5814 return NULL;
5815
5816 *iter = &upper->list;
5817
5818 return upper->dev;
5819}
5820EXPORT_SYMBOL(netdev_upper_get_next_dev_rcu);
5821
5822static struct net_device *netdev_next_upper_dev_rcu(struct net_device *dev,
5823 struct list_head **iter)
5824{
5825 struct netdev_adjacent *upper;
5826
5827 WARN_ON_ONCE(!rcu_read_lock_held() && !lockdep_rtnl_is_held());
5828
5829 upper = list_entry_rcu((*iter)->next, struct netdev_adjacent, list);
5830
5831 if (&upper->list == &dev->adj_list.upper)
5832 return NULL;
5833
5834 *iter = &upper->list;
5835
5836 return upper->dev;
5837}
5838
5839int netdev_walk_all_upper_dev_rcu(struct net_device *dev,
5840 int (*fn)(struct net_device *dev,
5841 void *data),
5842 void *data)
5843{
5844 struct net_device *udev;
5845 struct list_head *iter;
5846 int ret;
5847
5848 for (iter = &dev->adj_list.upper,
5849 udev = netdev_next_upper_dev_rcu(dev, &iter);
5850 udev;
5851 udev = netdev_next_upper_dev_rcu(dev, &iter)) {
5852 /* first is the upper device itself */
5853 ret = fn(udev, data);
5854 if (ret)
5855 return ret;
5856
5857 /* then look at all of its upper devices */
5858 ret = netdev_walk_all_upper_dev_rcu(udev, fn, data);
5859 if (ret)
5860 return ret;
5861 }
5862
5863 return 0;
5864}
5865EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(netdev_walk_all_upper_dev_rcu);
5866
5867/**
5868 * netdev_lower_get_next_private - Get the next ->private from the
5869 * lower neighbour list
5870 * @dev: device
5871 * @iter: list_head ** of the current position
5872 *
5873 * Gets the next netdev_adjacent->private from the dev's lower neighbour
5874 * list, starting from iter position. The caller must hold either hold the
5875 * RTNL lock or its own locking that guarantees that the neighbour lower
5876 * list will remain unchanged.
5877 */
5878void *netdev_lower_get_next_private(struct net_device *dev,
5879 struct list_head **iter)
5880{
5881 struct netdev_adjacent *lower;
5882
5883 lower = list_entry(*iter, struct netdev_adjacent, list);
5884
5885 if (&lower->list == &dev->adj_list.lower)
5886 return NULL;
5887
5888 *iter = lower->list.next;
5889
5890 return lower->private;
5891}
5892EXPORT_SYMBOL(netdev_lower_get_next_private);

5963int netdev_walk_all_lower_dev(struct net_device *dev,
5964 int (*fn)(struct net_device *dev,
5965 void *data),
5966 void *data)
5967{
5968 struct net_device *ldev;
5969 struct list_head *iter;
5970 int ret;
5971
5972 for (iter = &dev->adj_list.lower,
5973 ldev = netdev_next_lower_dev(dev, &iter);
5974 ldev;
5975 ldev = netdev_next_lower_dev(dev, &iter)) {
5976 /* first is the lower device itself */
5977 ret = fn(ldev, data);
5978 if (ret)
5979 return ret;
5980
5981 /* then look at all of its lower devices */
5982 ret = netdev_walk_all_lower_dev(ldev, fn, data);
5983 if (ret)
5984 return ret;
5985 }
5986
5987 return 0;
5988}
