6073static int netdev_adjacent_sysfs_add(struct net_device *dev,
6074 struct net_device *adj_dev,
6075 struct list_head *dev_list)
6076{
6077 char linkname[IFNAMSIZ+7];
6078
6079 sprintf(linkname, dev_list == &dev->adj_list.upper ?
6080 "upper_%s" : "lower_%s", adj_dev->name);
6081 return sysfs_create_link(&(dev->dev.kobj), &(adj_dev->dev.kobj),
6082 linkname);
6083}
6084static void netdev_adjacent_sysfs_del(struct net_device *dev,
6085 char *name,
6086 struct list_head *dev_list)
6087{
6088 char linkname[IFNAMSIZ+7];
6089
6090 sprintf(linkname, dev_list == &dev->adj_list.upper ?
6091 "upper_%s" : "lower_%s", name);
6092 sysfs_remove_link(&(dev->dev.kobj), linkname);
6093}
6094
6095static inline bool netdev_adjacent_is_neigh_list(struct net_device *dev,
6096 struct net_device *adj_dev,
6097 struct list_head *dev_list)
6098{
6099 return (dev_list == &dev->adj_list.upper ||
6100 dev_list == &dev->adj_list.lower) &&
6101 net_eq(dev_net(dev), dev_net(adj_dev));
6102}
6103
6104static int __netdev_adjacent_dev_insert(struct net_device *dev,
6105 struct net_device *adj_dev,
6106 struct list_head *dev_list,
6107 void *private, bool master)
6108{
6109 struct netdev_adjacent *adj;
6110 int ret;
6111
6112 adj = __netdev_find_adj(adj_dev, dev_list);
6113
6114 if (adj) {
6115 adj->ref_nr += 1;
6116 pr_debug("Insert adjacency: dev %s adj_dev %s adj->ref_nr %d\n",
6117 dev->name, adj_dev->name, adj->ref_nr);
6118
6119 return 0;
6120 }
6121
6122 adj = kmalloc(sizeof(*adj), GFP_KERNEL);
6123 if (!adj)
6124 return -ENOMEM;
6125
6126 adj->dev = adj_dev;
6127 adj->master = master;
6128 adj->ref_nr = 1;
6129 adj->private = private;
6130 dev_hold(adj_dev);
6131
6132 pr_debug("Insert adjacency: dev %s adj_dev %s adj->ref_nr %d; dev_hold on %s\n",
6133 dev->name, adj_dev->name, adj->ref_nr, adj_dev->name);
6134
6135 if (netdev_adjacent_is_neigh_list(dev, adj_dev, dev_list)) {
6136 ret = netdev_adjacent_sysfs_add(dev, adj_dev, dev_list);
6137 if (ret)
6138 goto free_adj;
6139 }
6140
6141 /* Ensure that master link is always the first item in list. */
6142 if (master) {
6143 ret = sysfs_create_link(&(dev->dev.kobj),
6144 &(adj_dev->dev.kobj), "master");
6145 if (ret)
6146 goto remove_symlinks;
6147
6148 list_add_rcu(&adj->list, dev_list);
6149 } else {
6150 list_add_tail_rcu(&adj->list, dev_list);
6151 }
6152
6153 return 0;
6154
6155remove_symlinks:
6156 if (netdev_adjacent_is_neigh_list(dev, adj_dev, dev_list))
6157 netdev_adjacent_sysfs_del(dev, adj_dev->name, dev_list);
6158free_adj:
6159 kfree(adj);
6160 dev_put(adj_dev);
6161
6162 return ret;
6163}
6164
6165static void __netdev_adjacent_dev_remove(struct net_device *dev,
6166 struct net_device *adj_dev,
6167 u16 ref_nr,
6168 struct list_head *dev_list)
6169{
6170 struct netdev_adjacent *adj;
6171
6172 pr_debug("Remove adjacency: dev %s adj_dev %s ref_nr %d\n",
6173 dev->name, adj_dev->name, ref_nr);
6174
6175 adj = __netdev_find_adj(adj_dev, dev_list);
6176
6177 if (!adj) {
6178 pr_err("Adjacency does not exist for device %s from %s\n",
6179 dev->name, adj_dev->name);
6180 WARN_ON(1);
6181 return;
6182 }
6183
6184 if (adj->ref_nr > ref_nr) {
6185 pr_debug("adjacency: %s to %s ref_nr - %d = %d\n",
6186 dev->name, adj_dev->name, ref_nr,
6187 adj->ref_nr - ref_nr);
6188 adj->ref_nr -= ref_nr;
6189 return;
6190 }
6191
6192 if (adj->master)
6193 sysfs_remove_link(&(dev->dev.kobj), "master");
6194
6195 if (netdev_adjacent_is_neigh_list(dev, adj_dev, dev_list))
6196 netdev_adjacent_sysfs_del(dev, adj_dev->name, dev_list);
6197
6198 list_del_rcu(&adj->list);
6199 pr_debug("adjacency: dev_put for %s, because link removed from %s to %s\n",
6200 adj_dev->name, dev->name, adj_dev->name);
6201 dev_put(adj_dev);
6202 kfree_rcu(adj, rcu);
6203}
6204
6205static int __netdev_adjacent_dev_link_lists(struct net_device *dev,
6206 struct net_device *upper_dev,
6207 struct list_head *up_list,
6208 struct list_head *down_list,
6209 void *private, bool master)
6210{
6211 int ret;
6212
6213 ret = __netdev_adjacent_dev_insert(dev, upper_dev, up_list,
6214 private, master);
6215 if (ret)
6216 return ret;
6217
6218 ret = __netdev_adjacent_dev_insert(upper_dev, dev, down_list,
6219 private, false);
6220 if (ret) {
6221 __netdev_adjacent_dev_remove(dev, upper_dev, 1, up_list);
6222 return ret;
6223 }
6224
6225 return 0;
6226}
6227
6228static void __netdev_adjacent_dev_unlink_lists(struct net_device *dev,
6229 struct net_device *upper_dev,
6230 u16 ref_nr,
6231 struct list_head *up_list,
6232 struct list_head *down_list)
6233{
6234 __netdev_adjacent_dev_remove(dev, upper_dev, ref_nr, up_list);
6235 __netdev_adjacent_dev_remove(upper_dev, dev, ref_nr, down_list);
6236}
6237
6238static int __netdev_adjacent_dev_link_neighbour(struct net_device *dev,
6239 struct net_device *upper_dev,
6240 void *private, bool master)
6241{
6242 return __netdev_adjacent_dev_link_lists(dev, upper_dev,
6243 &dev->adj_list.upper,
6244 &upper_dev->adj_list.lower,
6245 private, master);
6246}
6247
6248static void __netdev_adjacent_dev_unlink_neighbour(struct net_device *dev,
6249 struct net_device *upper_dev)
6250{
6251 __netdev_adjacent_dev_unlink_lists(dev, upper_dev, 1,
6252 &dev->adj_list.upper,
6253 &upper_dev->adj_list.lower);
6254}
6255
6256static int __netdev_upper_dev_link(struct net_device *dev,
6257 struct net_device *upper_dev, bool master,
6258 void *upper_priv, void *upper_info)
6259{
6260 struct netdev_notifier_changeupper_info changeupper_info;
6261 int ret = 0;
6262
6263 ASSERT_RTNL();
6264
6265 if (dev == upper_dev)
6266 return -EBUSY;
6267
6268 /* To prevent loops, check if dev is not upper device to upper_dev. */
6269 if (netdev_has_upper_dev(upper_dev, dev))
6270 return -EBUSY;
6271
6272 if (netdev_has_upper_dev(dev, upper_dev))
6273 return -EEXIST;
6274
6275 if (master && netdev_master_upper_dev_get(dev))
6276 return -EBUSY;
6277
6278 changeupper_info.upper_dev = upper_dev;
6279 changeupper_info.master = master;
6280 changeupper_info.linking = true;
6281 changeupper_info.upper_info = upper_info;
6282
6283 ret = call_netdevice_notifiers_info(NETDEV_PRECHANGEUPPER, dev,
6284 &changeupper_info.info);
6285 ret = notifier_to_errno(ret);
6286 if (ret)
6287 return ret;
6288
6289 ret = __netdev_adjacent_dev_link_neighbour(dev, upper_dev, upper_priv,
6290 master);
6291 if (ret)
6292 return ret;
6293
6294 ret = call_netdevice_notifiers_info(NETDEV_CHANGEUPPER, dev,
6295 &changeupper_info.info);
6296 ret = notifier_to_errno(ret);
6297 if (ret)
6298 goto rollback;
6299
6300 return 0;
6301
6302rollback:
6303 __netdev_adjacent_dev_unlink_neighbour(dev, upper_dev);
6304
6305 return ret;
6306}
6307
6308/**
6309 * netdev_upper_dev_link - Add a link to the upper device
6310 * @dev: device
6311 * @upper_dev: new upper device
6312 *
6313 * Adds a link to device which is upper to this one. The caller must hold
6314 * the RTNL lock. On a failure a negative errno code is returned.
6315 * On success the reference counts are adjusted and the function
6316 * returns zero.
6317 */
6318int netdev_upper_dev_link(struct net_device *dev,
6319 struct net_device *upper_dev)
6320{
6321 return __netdev_upper_dev_link(dev, upper_dev, false, NULL, NULL);
6322}
6323EXPORT_SYMBOL(netdev_upper_dev_link);
6324
6325/**
6326 * netdev_master_upper_dev_link - Add a master link to the upper device
6327 * @dev: device
6328 * @upper_dev: new upper device
6329 * @upper_priv: upper device private
6330 * @upper_info: upper info to be passed down via notifier
6331 *
6332 * Adds a link to device which is upper to this one. In this case, only
6333 * one master upper device can be linked, although other non-master devices
6334 * might be linked as well. The caller must hold the RTNL lock.
6335 * On a failure a negative errno code is returned. On success the reference
6336 * counts are adjusted and the function returns zero.
6337 */
6338int netdev_master_upper_dev_link(struct net_device *dev,
6339 struct net_device *upper_dev,
6340 void *upper_priv, void *upper_info)
6341{
6342 return __netdev_upper_dev_link(dev, upper_dev, true,
6343 upper_priv, upper_info);
6344}
6345EXPORT_SYMBOL(netdev_master_upper_dev_link);
6346
6347/**
6348 * netdev_upper_dev_unlink - Removes a link to upper device
6349 * @dev: device
6350 * @upper_dev: new upper device
6351 *
6352 * Removes a link to device which is upper to this one. The caller must hold
6353 * the RTNL lock.
6354 */
6355void netdev_upper_dev_unlink(struct net_device *dev,
6356 struct net_device *upper_dev)
6357{
6358 struct netdev_notifier_changeupper_info changeupper_info;
6359
6360 ASSERT_RTNL();
6361
6362 changeupper_info.upper_dev = upper_dev;
6363 changeupper_info.master = netdev_master_upper_dev_get(dev) == upper_dev;
6364 changeupper_info.linking = false;
6365
6366 call_netdevice_notifiers_info(NETDEV_PRECHANGEUPPER, dev,
6367 &changeupper_info.info);
6368
6369 __netdev_adjacent_dev_unlink_neighbour(dev, upper_dev);
6370
6371 call_netdevice_notifiers_info(NETDEV_CHANGEUPPER, dev,
6372 &changeupper_info.info);
6373}
6374EXPORT_SYMBOL(netdev_upper_dev_unlink);

6396static void netdev_adjacent_add_links(struct net_device *dev)
6397{
6398 struct netdev_adjacent *iter;
6399
6400 struct net *net = dev_net(dev);
6401
6402 list_for_each_entry(iter, &dev->adj_list.upper, list) {
6403 if (!net_eq(net, dev_net(iter->dev)))
6404 continue;
6405 netdev_adjacent_sysfs_add(iter->dev, dev,
6406 &iter->dev->adj_list.lower);
6407 netdev_adjacent_sysfs_add(dev, iter->dev,
6408 &dev->adj_list.upper);
6409 }
6410
6411 list_for_each_entry(iter, &dev->adj_list.lower, list) {
6412 if (!net_eq(net, dev_net(iter->dev)))
6413 continue;
6414 netdev_adjacent_sysfs_add(iter->dev, dev,
6415 &iter->dev->adj_list.upper);
6416 netdev_adjacent_sysfs_add(dev, iter->dev,
6417 &dev->adj_list.lower);
6418 }
6419}

6421static void netdev_adjacent_del_links(struct net_device *dev)

6431 &iter->dev->adj_list.lower);
6432 netdev_adjacent_sysfs_del(dev, iter->dev->name,

6439 netdev_adjacent_sysfs_del(iter->dev, dev->name,

6531 ops->ndo_change_rx_flags(dev, flags);

6533
6534static int __dev_set_promiscuity(struct net_device *dev, int inc, bool notify)
6535{
6536 unsigned int old_flags = dev->flags;
6537 kuid_t uid;
6538 kgid_t gid;
6539
6540 ASSERT_RTNL();
6541
6542 dev->flags |= IFF_PROMISC;
6543 dev->promiscuity += inc;
6544 if (dev->promiscuity == 0) {
6545 /*
6546 * Avoid overflow.
6547 * If inc causes overflow, untouch promisc and return error.
6548 */
6549 if (inc < 0)
6550 dev->flags &= ~IFF_PROMISC;
6551 else {
6552 dev->promiscuity -= inc;
6553 pr_warn("%s: promiscuity touches roof, set promiscuity failed. promiscuity feature of device might be broken.\n",
6554 dev->name);
6555 return -EOVERFLOW;
6556 }
6557 }
6558 if (dev->flags != old_flags) {
6559 pr_info("device %s %s promiscuous mode\n",
6560 dev->name,
6561 dev->flags & IFF_PROMISC ? "entered" : "left");
6562 if (audit_enabled) {
6563 current_uid_gid(&uid, &gid);
6564 audit_log(current->audit_context, GFP_ATOMIC,
6565 AUDIT_ANOM_PROMISCUOUS,
6566 "dev=%s prom=%d old_prom=%d auid=%u uid=%u gid=%u ses=%u",
6567 dev->name, (dev->flags & IFF_PROMISC),
6568 (old_flags & IFF_PROMISC),
6569 from_kuid(&init_user_ns, audit_get_loginuid(current)),
6570 from_kuid(&init_user_ns, uid),
6571 from_kgid(&init_user_ns, gid),
6572 audit_get_sessionid(current));
6573 }
6574
6575 dev_change_rx_flags(dev, IFF_PROMISC);
6576 }
6577 if (notify)
6578 __dev_notify_flags(dev, old_flags, IFF_PROMISC);
6579 return 0;
6580}
6581
6582/**
6583 * dev_set_promiscuity - update promiscuity count on a device
6584 * @dev: device
6585 * @inc: modifier
6586 *
6587 * Add or remove promiscuity from a device. While the count in the device
6588 * remains above zero the interface remains promiscuous. Once it hits zero
6589 * the device reverts back to normal filtering operation. A negative inc
6590 * value is used to drop promiscuity on the device.
6591 * Return 0 if successful or a negative errno code on error.
6592 */
6593int dev_set_promiscuity(struct net_device *dev, int inc)
6594{
6595 unsigned int old_flags = dev->flags;
6596 int err;
6597
6598 err = __dev_set_promiscuity(dev, inc, true);
6599 if (err < 0)
6600 return err;
6601 if (dev->flags != old_flags)
6602 dev_set_rx_mode(dev);
6603 return err;
6604}
6605EXPORT_SYMBOL(dev_set_promiscuity);
6606
6607static int __dev_set_allmulti(struct net_device *dev, int inc, bool notify)
6608{
6609 unsigned int old_flags = dev->flags, old_gflags = dev->gflags;
6610
6611 ASSERT_RTNL();
6612
6613 dev->flags |= IFF_ALLMULTI;
6614 dev->allmulti += inc;
6615 if (dev->allmulti == 0) {
6616 /*
6617 * Avoid overflow.
6618 * If inc causes overflow, untouch allmulti and return error.
6619 */
6620 if (inc < 0)
6621 dev->flags &= ~IFF_ALLMULTI;
6622 else {
6623 dev->allmulti -= inc;
6624 pr_warn("%s: allmulti touches roof, set allmulti failed. allmulti feature of device might be broken.\n",
6625 dev->name);
6626 return -EOVERFLOW;
6627 }
6628 }
6629 if (dev->flags ^ old_flags) {
6630 dev_change_rx_flags(dev, IFF_ALLMULTI);
6631 dev_set_rx_mode(dev);
6632 if (notify)
6633 __dev_notify_flags(dev, old_flags,
6634 dev->gflags ^ old_gflags);
6635 }
6636 return 0;
6637}
6638
6639/**
6640 * dev_set_allmulti - update allmulti count on a device
6641 * @dev: device
6642 * @inc: modifier
6643 *
6644 * Add or remove reception of all multicast frames to a device. While the
6645 * count in the device remains above zero the interface remains listening
6646 * to all interfaces. Once it hits zero the device reverts back to normal
6647 * filtering operation. A negative @inc value is used to drop the counter
6648 * when releasing a resource needing all multicasts.
6649 * Return 0 if successful or a negative errno code on error.
6650 */
6651
6652int dev_set_allmulti(struct net_device *dev, int inc)
6653{
6654 return __dev_set_allmulti(dev, inc, true);
6655}
6656EXPORT_SYMBOL(dev_set_allmulti);
6657
6658/*
6659 * Upload unicast and multicast address lists to device and
6660 * configure RX filtering. When the device doesn't support unicast
6661 * filtering it is put in promiscuous mode while unicast addresses
6662 * are present.
6663 */
6664void __dev_set_rx_mode(struct net_device *dev)
6665{
6666 const struct net_device_ops *ops = dev->netdev_ops;
6667
6668 /* dev_open will call this function so the list will stay sane. */
6669 if (!(dev->flags&IFF_UP))
6670 return;
6671
6672 if (!netif_device_present(dev))
6673 return;
6674
6675 if (!(dev->priv_flags & IFF_UNICAST_FLT)) {
6676 /* Unicast addresses changes may only happen under the rtnl,
6677 * therefore calling __dev_set_promiscuity here is safe.
6678 */
6679 if (!netdev_uc_empty(dev) && !dev->uc_promisc) {
6680 __dev_set_promiscuity(dev, 1, false);
6681 dev->uc_promisc = true;
6682 } else if (netdev_uc_empty(dev) && dev->uc_promisc) {
6683 __dev_set_promiscuity(dev, -1, false);
6684 dev->uc_promisc = false;
6685 }
6686 }
6687
6688 if (ops->ndo_set_rx_mode)
6689 ops->ndo_set_rx_mode(dev);
6690}
6691
6692void dev_set_rx_mode(struct net_device *dev)
6693{
6694 netif_addr_lock_bh(dev);
6695 __dev_set_rx_mode(dev);
6696 netif_addr_unlock_bh(dev);
6697}
6698
6699/**
6700 * dev_get_flags - get flags reported to userspace
6701 * @dev: device
6702 *
6703 * Get the combination of flag bits exported through APIs to userspace.
6704 */
6705unsigned int dev_get_flags(const struct net_device *dev)
6706{
6707 unsigned int flags;
6708
6709 flags = (dev->flags & ~(IFF_PROMISC |
6710 IFF_ALLMULTI |
6711 IFF_RUNNING |
6712 IFF_LOWER_UP |
6713 IFF_DORMANT)) |
6714 (dev->gflags & (IFF_PROMISC |
6715 IFF_ALLMULTI));
6716
6717 if (netif_running(dev)) {
6718 if (netif_oper_up(dev))
6719 flags |= IFF_RUNNING;
6720 if (netif_carrier_ok(dev))
6721 flags |= IFF_LOWER_UP;
6722 if (netif_dormant(dev))
6723 flags |= IFF_DORMANT;
6724 }
6725
6726 return flags;
6727}
6728EXPORT_SYMBOL(dev_get_flags);
6729
6730int __dev_change_flags(struct net_device *dev, unsigned int flags)
6731{
6732 unsigned int old_flags = dev->flags;
6733 int ret;
6734
6735 ASSERT_RTNL();
6736
6737 /*
6738 * Set the flags on our device.
6739 */
6740
6741 dev->flags = (flags & (IFF_DEBUG | IFF_NOTRAILERS | IFF_NOARP |
6742 IFF_DYNAMIC | IFF_MULTICAST | IFF_PORTSEL |
6743 IFF_AUTOMEDIA)) |
6744 (dev->flags & (IFF_UP | IFF_VOLATILE | IFF_PROMISC |
6745 IFF_ALLMULTI));
6746
6747 /*
6748 * Load in the correct multicast list now the flags have changed.
6749 */
6750
6751 if ((old_flags ^ flags) & IFF_MULTICAST)
6752 dev_change_rx_flags(dev, IFF_MULTICAST);
6753
6754 dev_set_rx_mode(dev);
6755
6756 /*
6757 * Have we downed the interface. We handle IFF_UP ourselves
6758 * according to user attempts to set it, rather than blindly
6759 * setting it.
6760 */
6761
6762 ret = 0;
6763 if ((old_flags ^ flags) & IFF_UP) {
6764 if (old_flags & IFF_UP)
6765 __dev_close(dev);
6766 else
6767 ret = __dev_open(dev);
6768 }
6769
6770 if ((flags ^ dev->gflags) & IFF_PROMISC) {
6771 int inc = (flags & IFF_PROMISC) ? 1 : -1;
6772 unsigned int old_flags = dev->flags;
6773
6774 dev->gflags ^= IFF_PROMISC;
6775
6776 if (__dev_set_promiscuity(dev, inc, false) >= 0)
6777 if (dev->flags != old_flags)
6778 dev_set_rx_mode(dev);
6779 }
6780
6781 /* NOTE: order of synchronization of IFF_PROMISC and IFF_ALLMULTI
6782 * is important. Some (broken) drivers set IFF_PROMISC, when
6783 * IFF_ALLMULTI is requested not asking us and not reporting.
6784 */
6785 if ((flags ^ dev->gflags) & IFF_ALLMULTI) {
6786 int inc = (flags & IFF_ALLMULTI) ? 1 : -1;
6787
6788 dev->gflags ^= IFF_ALLMULTI;
6789 __dev_set_allmulti(dev, inc, false);
6790 }
6791
6792 return ret;
6793}
6794
6795void __dev_notify_flags(struct net_device *dev, unsigned int old_flags,
6796 unsigned int gchanges)
6797{
6798 unsigned int changes = dev->flags ^ old_flags;
6799
6800 if (gchanges)
6801 rtmsg_ifinfo(RTM_NEWLINK, dev, gchanges, GFP_ATOMIC);
6802
6803 if (changes & IFF_UP) {
6804 if (dev->flags & IFF_UP)
6805 call_netdevice_notifiers(NETDEV_UP, dev);
6806 else
6807 call_netdevice_notifiers(NETDEV_DOWN, dev);
6808 }
6809
6810 if (dev->flags & IFF_UP &&
6811 (changes & ~(IFF_UP | IFF_PROMISC | IFF_ALLMULTI | IFF_VOLATILE))) {
6812 struct netdev_notifier_change_info change_info;
6813
6814 change_info.flags_changed = changes;
6815 call_netdevice_notifiers_info(NETDEV_CHANGE, dev,
6816 &change_info.info);
6817 }
6818}
6819
6820/**
6821 * dev_change_flags - change device settings
6822 * @dev: device
6823 * @flags: device state flags
6824 *
6825 * Change settings on device based state flags. The flags are
6826 * in the userspace exported format.
6827 */
6828int dev_change_flags(struct net_device *dev, unsigned int flags)
6829{
6830 int ret;
6831 unsigned int changes, old_flags = dev->flags, old_gflags = dev->gflags;
6832
6833 ret = __dev_change_flags(dev, flags);
6834 if (ret < 0)
6835 return ret;
6836
6837 changes = (old_flags ^ dev->flags) | (old_gflags ^ dev->gflags);
6838 __dev_notify_flags(dev, old_flags, changes);
6839 return ret;
6840}
6841EXPORT_SYMBOL(dev_change_flags);
6842
6843int __dev_set_mtu(struct net_device *dev, int new_mtu)
6844{
6845 const struct net_device_ops *ops = dev->netdev_ops;
6846
6847 if (ops->ndo_change_mtu)
6848 return ops->ndo_change_mtu(dev, new_mtu);
6849
6850 dev->mtu = new_mtu;
6851 return 0;
6852}
6853EXPORT_SYMBOL(__dev_set_mtu);
6854
6855/**
6856 * dev_set_mtu - Change maximum transfer unit
6857 * @dev: device
6858 * @new_mtu: new transfer unit
6859 *
6860 * Change the maximum transfer size of the network device.
6861 */
6862int dev_set_mtu(struct net_device *dev, int new_mtu)
6863{
6864 int err, orig_mtu;
6865
6866 if (new_mtu == dev->mtu)
6867 return 0;
6868
6869 /* MTU must be positive, and in range */
6870 if (new_mtu < 0 || new_mtu < dev->min_mtu) {
6871 net_err_ratelimited("%s: Invalid MTU %d requested, hw min %d\n",
6872 dev->name, new_mtu, dev->min_mtu);
6873 return -EINVAL;
6874 }
6875
6876 if (dev->max_mtu > 0 && new_mtu > dev->max_mtu) {
6877 net_err_ratelimited("%s: Invalid MTU %d requested, hw max %d\n",
6878 dev->name, new_mtu, dev->max_mtu);
6879 return -EINVAL;
6880 }
6881
6882 if (!netif_device_present(dev))
6883 return -ENODEV;
6884
6885 err = call_netdevice_notifiers(NETDEV_PRECHANGEMTU, dev);
6886 err = notifier_to_errno(err);
6887 if (err)
6888 return err;
6889
6890 orig_mtu = dev->mtu;
6891 err = __dev_set_mtu(dev, new_mtu);
6892
6893 if (!err) {
6894 err = call_netdevice_notifiers(NETDEV_CHANGEMTU, dev);
6895 err = notifier_to_errno(err);
6896 if (err) {
6897 /* setting mtu back and notifying everyone again,
6898 * so that they have a chance to revert changes.
6899 */
6900 __dev_set_mtu(dev, orig_mtu);
6901 call_netdevice_notifiers(NETDEV_CHANGEMTU, dev);
6902 }
6903 }
6904 return err;
6905}
6906EXPORT_SYMBOL(dev_set_mtu);
6907
6908/**
6909 * dev_set_group - Change group this device belongs to
6910 * @dev: device
6911 * @new_group: group this device should belong to
6912 */
6913void dev_set_group(struct net_device *dev, int new_group)
6914{
6915 dev->group = new_group;
6916}
6917EXPORT_SYMBOL(dev_set_group);

6919/**
6920 * dev_set_mac_address - Change Media Access Control Address
6921 * @dev: device
6922 * @sa: new address
6923 *
6924 * Change the hardware (MAC) address of the device
6925 */
6926int dev_set_mac_address(struct net_device *dev, struct sockaddr *sa)
6927{
6928 const struct net_device_ops *ops = dev->netdev_ops;

6930

6933 if (sa->sa_family != dev->type)
6934 return -EINVAL;
6935 if (!netif_device_present(dev))
6936 return -ENODEV;

6938 if (err)
6939 return err;
6940 dev->addr_assign_type = NET_ADDR_SET;
6941 call_netdevice_notifiers(NETDEV_CHANGEADDR, dev);
6942 add_device_randomness(dev->dev_addr, dev->addr_len);
6943 return 0;
6944}
6945EXPORT_SYMBOL(dev_set_mac_address);

7022
7023u8 __dev_xdp_attached(struct net_device *dev, xdp_op_t xdp_op, u32 *prog_id)
7024{
7025 struct netdev_xdp xdp;
7026
7027 memset(&xdp, 0, sizeof(xdp));
7028 xdp.command = XDP_QUERY_PROG;
7029
7030 /* Query must always succeed. */
7031 WARN_ON(xdp_op(dev, &xdp) < 0);
7032 if (prog_id)
7033 *prog_id = xdp.prog_id;
7034
7035 return xdp.prog_attached;
7036}
7037
7038static int dev_xdp_install(struct net_device *dev, xdp_op_t xdp_op,
7039 struct netlink_ext_ack *extack, u32 flags,
7040 struct bpf_prog *prog)
7041{
7042 struct netdev_xdp xdp;
7043
7044 memset(&xdp, 0, sizeof(xdp));
7045 if (flags & XDP_FLAGS_HW_MODE)
7046 xdp.command = XDP_SETUP_PROG_HW;
7047 else
7048 xdp.command = XDP_SETUP_PROG;
7049 xdp.extack = extack;
7050 xdp.flags = flags;
7051 xdp.prog = prog;
7052
7053 return xdp_op(dev, &xdp);
7054}
7055
7056/**
7057 * dev_change_xdp_fd - set or clear a bpf program for a device rx path
7058 * @dev: device
7059 * @extack: netlink extended ack
7060 * @fd: new program fd or negative value to clear
7061 * @flags: xdp-related flags
7062 *
7063 * Set or clear a bpf program for a device
7064 */
7065int dev_change_xdp_fd(struct net_device *dev, struct netlink_ext_ack *extack,
7066 int fd, u32 flags)
7067{
7068 const struct net_device_ops *ops = dev->netdev_ops;
7069 struct bpf_prog *prog = NULL;
7070 xdp_op_t xdp_op, xdp_chk;
7071 int err;
7072
7073 ASSERT_RTNL();
7074
7075 xdp_op = xdp_chk = ops->ndo_xdp;
7076 if (!xdp_op && (flags & (XDP_FLAGS_DRV_MODE | XDP_FLAGS_HW_MODE)))
7077 return -EOPNOTSUPP;
7078 if (!xdp_op || (flags & XDP_FLAGS_SKB_MODE))
7079 xdp_op = generic_xdp_install;
7080 if (xdp_op == xdp_chk)
7081 xdp_chk = generic_xdp_install;
7082
7083 if (fd >= 0) {
7084 if (xdp_chk && __dev_xdp_attached(dev, xdp_chk, NULL))
7085 return -EEXIST;
7086 if ((flags & XDP_FLAGS_UPDATE_IF_NOEXIST) &&
7087 __dev_xdp_attached(dev, xdp_op, NULL))
7088 return -EBUSY;
7089
7090 prog = bpf_prog_get_type(fd, BPF_PROG_TYPE_XDP);
7091 if (IS_ERR(prog))
7092 return PTR_ERR(prog);
7093 }
7094
7095 err = dev_xdp_install(dev, xdp_op, extack, flags, prog);
7096 if (err < 0 && prog)
7097 bpf_prog_put(prog);
7098
7099 return err;
7100}
7101
7102/**
7103 * dev_new_index - allocate an ifindex
7104 * @net: the applicable net namespace
7105 *
7106 * Returns a suitable unique value for a new device interface
7107 * number. The caller must hold the rtnl semaphore or the
7108 * dev_base_lock to be sure it remains unique.
7109 */
7110static int dev_new_index(struct net *net)
7111{
7112 int ifindex = net->ifindex;
7113
7114 for (;;) {
7115 if (++ifindex <= 0)
7116 ifindex = 1;
7117 if (!__dev_get_by_index(net, ifindex))
7118 return net->ifindex = ifindex;
7119 }
7120}
7121
7122/* Delayed registration/unregisteration */
7123static LIST_HEAD(net_todo_list);
7124DECLARE_WAIT_QUEUE_HEAD(netdev_unregistering_wq);
7125
7126static void net_set_todo(struct net_device *dev)
7127{
7128 list_add_tail(&dev->todo_list, &net_todo_list);
7129 dev_net(dev)->dev_unreg_count++;
7130}
7131
7132static void rollback_registered_many(struct list_head *head)
7133{
7134 struct net_device *dev, *tmp;
7135 LIST_HEAD(close_head);
7136
7137 BUG_ON(dev_boot_phase);
7138 ASSERT_RTNL();
7139
7140 list_for_each_entry_safe(dev, tmp, head, unreg_list) {
7141 /* Some devices call without registering
7142 * for initialization unwind. Remove those
7143 * devices and proceed with the remaining.
7144 */
7145 if (dev->reg_state == NETREG_UNINITIALIZED) {
7146 pr_debug("unregister_netdevice: device %s/%p never was registered\n",
7147 dev->name, dev);
7148
7149 WARN_ON(1);
7150 list_del(&dev->unreg_list);
7151 continue;
7152 }
7153 dev->dismantle = true;
7154 BUG_ON(dev->reg_state != NETREG_REGISTERED);
7155 }
7156
7157 /* If device is running, close it first. */
7158 list_for_each_entry(dev, head, unreg_list)
7159 list_add_tail(&dev->close_list, &close_head);
7160 dev_close_many(&close_head, true);
7161
7162 list_for_each_entry(dev, head, unreg_list) {
7163 /* And unlink it from device chain. */
7164 unlist_netdevice(dev);
7165
7166 dev->reg_state = NETREG_UNREGISTERING;
7167 }
7168 flush_all_backlogs();
7169
7170 synchronize_net();
7171
7172 list_for_each_entry(dev, head, unreg_list) {
7173 struct sk_buff *skb = NULL;
7174
7175 /* Shutdown queueing discipline. */
7176 dev_shutdown(dev);
7177
7178
7179 /* Notify protocols, that we are about to destroy
7180 * this device. They should clean all the things.
7181 */
7182 call_netdevice_notifiers(NETDEV_UNREGISTER, dev);
7183
7184 if (!dev->rtnl_link_ops ||
7185 dev->rtnl_link_state == RTNL_LINK_INITIALIZED)
7186 skb = rtmsg_ifinfo_build_skb(RTM_DELLINK, dev, ~0U, 0,
7187 GFP_KERNEL);
7188
7189 /*
7190 * Flush the unicast and multicast chains
7191 */
7192 dev_uc_flush(dev);
7193 dev_mc_flush(dev);
7194
7195 if (dev->netdev_ops->ndo_uninit)
7196 dev->netdev_ops->ndo_uninit(dev);
7197
7198 if (skb)
7199 rtmsg_ifinfo_send(skb, dev, GFP_KERNEL);
7200
7201 /* Notifier chain MUST detach us all upper devices. */
7202 WARN_ON(netdev_has_any_upper_dev(dev));
7203 WARN_ON(netdev_has_any_lower_dev(dev));
7204
7205 /* Remove entries from kobject tree */
7206 netdev_unregister_kobject(dev);
7207#ifdef CONFIG_XPS
7208 /* Remove XPS queueing entries */
7209 netif_reset_xps_queues_gt(dev, 0);
7210#endif
7211 }
7212
7213 synchronize_net();
7214
7215 list_for_each_entry(dev, head, unreg_list)
7216 dev_put(dev);
7217}
7218
7219static void rollback_registered(struct net_device *dev)
7220{
7221 LIST_HEAD(single);
7222
7223 list_add(&dev->unreg_list, &single);
7224 rollback_registered_many(&single);
7225 list_del(&single);
7226}
7227
7228static netdev_features_t netdev_sync_upper_features(struct net_device *lower,
7229 struct net_device *upper, netdev_features_t features)
7230{
7231 netdev_features_t upper_disables = NETIF_F_UPPER_DISABLES;
7232 netdev_features_t feature;
7233 int feature_bit;
7234
7235 for_each_netdev_feature(&upper_disables, feature_bit) {
7236 feature = __NETIF_F_BIT(feature_bit);
7237 if (!(upper->wanted_features & feature)
7238 && (features & feature)) {
7239 netdev_dbg(lower, "Dropping feature %pNF, upper dev %s has it off.\n",
7240 &feature, upper->name);
7241 features &= ~feature;
7242 }
7243 }
7244
7245 return features;
7246}
7247
7248static void netdev_sync_lower_features(struct net_device *upper,
7249 struct net_device *lower, netdev_features_t features)
7250{
7251 netdev_features_t upper_disables = NETIF_F_UPPER_DISABLES;
7252 netdev_features_t feature;
7253 int feature_bit;
7254
7255 for_each_netdev_feature(&upper_disables, feature_bit) {
7256 feature = __NETIF_F_BIT(feature_bit);
7257 if (!(features & feature) && (lower->features & feature)) {
7258 netdev_dbg(upper, "Disabling feature %pNF on lower dev %s.\n",
7259 &feature, lower->name);
7260 lower->wanted_features &= ~feature;
7261 netdev_update_features(lower);
7262
7263 if (unlikely(lower->features & feature))
7264 netdev_WARN(upper, "failed to disable %pNF on %s!\n",
7265 &feature, lower->name);
7266 }
7267 }
7268}
7269
7270static netdev_features_t netdev_fix_features(struct net_device *dev,
7271 netdev_features_t features)
7272{
7273 /* Fix illegal checksum combinations */
7274 if ((features & NETIF_F_HW_CSUM) &&
7275 (features & (NETIF_F_IP_CSUM|NETIF_F_IPV6_CSUM))) {
7276 netdev_warn(dev, "mixed HW and IP checksum settings.\n");
7277 features &= ~(NETIF_F_IP_CSUM|NETIF_F_IPV6_CSUM);
7278 }
7279
7280 /* TSO requires that SG is present as well. */
7281 if ((features & NETIF_F_ALL_TSO) && !(features & NETIF_F_SG)) {
7282 netdev_dbg(dev, "Dropping TSO features since no SG feature.\n");
7283 features &= ~NETIF_F_ALL_TSO;
7284 }
7285
7286 if ((features & NETIF_F_TSO) && !(features & NETIF_F_HW_CSUM) &&
7287 !(features & NETIF_F_IP_CSUM)) {
7288 netdev_dbg(dev, "Dropping TSO features since no CSUM feature.\n");
7289 features &= ~NETIF_F_TSO;
7290 features &= ~NETIF_F_TSO_ECN;
7291 }
7292
7293 if ((features & NETIF_F_TSO6) && !(features & NETIF_F_HW_CSUM) &&
7294 !(features & NETIF_F_IPV6_CSUM)) {
7295 netdev_dbg(dev, "Dropping TSO6 features since no CSUM feature.\n");
7296 features &= ~NETIF_F_TSO6;
7297 }
7298
7299 /* TSO with IPv4 ID mangling requires IPv4 TSO be enabled */
7300 if ((features & NETIF_F_TSO_MANGLEID) && !(features & NETIF_F_TSO))
7301 features &= ~NETIF_F_TSO_MANGLEID;
7302
7303 /* TSO ECN requires that TSO is present as well. */
7304 if ((features & NETIF_F_ALL_TSO) == NETIF_F_TSO_ECN)
7305 features &= ~NETIF_F_TSO_ECN;
7306
7307 /* Software GSO depends on SG. */
7308 if ((features & NETIF_F_GSO) && !(features & NETIF_F_SG)) {
7309 netdev_dbg(dev, "Dropping NETIF_F_GSO since no SG feature.\n");
7310 features &= ~NETIF_F_GSO;
7311 }
7312
7313 /* GSO partial features require GSO partial be set */
7314 if ((features & dev->gso_partial_features) &&
7315 !(features & NETIF_F_GSO_PARTIAL)) {
7316 netdev_dbg(dev,
7317 "Dropping partially supported GSO features since no GSO partial.\n");
7318 features &= ~dev->gso_partial_features;
7319 }
7320
7321 return features;
7322}
7323
7324int __netdev_update_features(struct net_device *dev)
7325{
7326 struct net_device *upper, *lower;
7327 netdev_features_t features;
7328 struct list_head *iter;
7329 int err = -1;
7330
7331 ASSERT_RTNL();
7332
7333 features = netdev_get_wanted_features(dev);
7334
7335 if (dev->netdev_ops->ndo_fix_features)
7336 features = dev->netdev_ops->ndo_fix_features(dev, features);
7337
7338 /* driver might be less strict about feature dependencies */
7339 features = netdev_fix_features(dev, features);
7340
7341 /* some features can't be enabled if they're off an an upper device */
7342 netdev_for_each_upper_dev_rcu(dev, upper, iter)
7343 features = netdev_sync_upper_features(dev, upper, features);
7344
7345 if (dev->features == features)
7346 goto sync_lower;
7347
7348 netdev_dbg(dev, "Features changed: %pNF -> %pNF\n",
7349 &dev->features, &features);
7350
7351 if (dev->netdev_ops->ndo_set_features)
7352 err = dev->netdev_ops->ndo_set_features(dev, features);
7353 else
7354 err = 0;
7355
7356 if (unlikely(err < 0)) {
7357 netdev_err(dev,
7358 "set_features() failed (%d); wanted %pNF, left %pNF\n",
7359 err, &features, &dev->features);
7360 /* return non-0 since some features might have changed and
7361 * it's better to fire a spurious notification than miss it
7362 */
7363 return -1;
7364 }
7365
7366sync_lower:
7367 /* some features must be disabled on lower devices when disabled
7368 * on an upper device (think: bonding master or bridge)
7369 */
7370 netdev_for_each_lower_dev(dev, lower, iter)
7371 netdev_sync_lower_features(dev, lower, features);
7372
7373 if (!err) {
7374 netdev_features_t diff = features ^ dev->features;
7375
7376 if (diff & NETIF_F_RX_UDP_TUNNEL_PORT) {
7377 /* udp_tunnel_{get,drop}_rx_info both need
7378 * NETIF_F_RX_UDP_TUNNEL_PORT enabled on the
7379 * device, or they won't do anything.
7380 * Thus we need to update dev->features
7381 * *before* calling udp_tunnel_get_rx_info,
7382 * but *after* calling udp_tunnel_drop_rx_info.
7383 */
7384 if (features & NETIF_F_RX_UDP_TUNNEL_PORT) {
7385 dev->features = features;
7386 udp_tunnel_get_rx_info(dev);
7387 } else {
7388 udp_tunnel_drop_rx_info(dev);
7389 }
7390 }
7391
7392 dev->features = features;
7393 }
7394
7395 return err < 0 ? 0 : 1;
7396}
7397
7398/**
7399 * netdev_update_features - recalculate device features
7400 * @dev: the device to check
7401 *
7402 * Recalculate dev->features set and send notifications if it
7403 * has changed. Should be called after driver or hardware dependent
7404 * conditions might have changed that influence the features.
7405 */
7406void netdev_update_features(struct net_device *dev)
7407{
7408 if (__netdev_update_features(dev))
7409 netdev_features_change(dev);
7410}
7411EXPORT_SYMBOL(netdev_update_features);
7412
7413/**
7414 * netdev_change_features - recalculate device features
7415 * @dev: the device to check
7416 *
7417 * Recalculate dev->features set and send notifications even
7418 * if they have not changed. Should be called instead of
7419 * netdev_update_features() if also dev->vlan_features might
7420 * have changed to allow the changes to be propagated to stacked
7421 * VLAN devices.
7422 */
7423void netdev_change_features(struct net_device *dev)
7424{
7425 __netdev_update_features(dev);
7426 netdev_features_change(dev);
7427}
7428EXPORT_SYMBOL(netdev_change_features);
7429
7430/**
7431 * netif_stacked_transfer_operstate - transfer operstate
7432 * @rootdev: the root or lower level device to transfer state from
7433 * @dev: the device to transfer operstate to
7434 *
7435 * Transfer operational state from root to device. This is normally
7436 * called when a stacking relationship exists between the root
7437 * device and the device(a leaf device).
7438 */
7439void netif_stacked_transfer_operstate(const struct net_device *rootdev,
7440 struct net_device *dev)
7441{
7442 if (rootdev->operstate == IF_OPER_DORMANT)
7443 netif_dormant_on(dev);
7444 else
7445 netif_dormant_off(dev);
7446
7447 if (netif_carrier_ok(rootdev))
7448 netif_carrier_on(dev);
7449 else
7450 netif_carrier_off(dev);
7451}
7452EXPORT_SYMBOL(netif_stacked_transfer_operstate);

7454#ifdef CONFIG_SYSFS
7455static int netif_alloc_rx_queues(struct net_device *dev)
7456{
7457 unsigned int i, count = dev->num_rx_queues;
7458 struct netdev_rx_queue *rx;
7459 size_t sz = count * sizeof(*rx);
7460
7461 BUG_ON(count < 1);
7462
7463 rx = kvzalloc(sz, GFP_KERNEL | __GFP_RETRY_MAYFAIL);
7464 if (!rx)
7465 return -ENOMEM;
7466
7467 dev->_rx = rx;
7468
7469 for (i = 0; i < count; i++)
7470 rx[i].dev = dev;
7471 return 0;
7472}
7473#endif
7474
7475static void netdev_init_one_queue(struct net_device *dev,
7476 struct netdev_queue *queue, void *_unused)
7477{
7478 /* Initialize queue lock */
7479 spin_lock_init(&queue->_xmit_lock);
7480 netdev_set_xmit_lockdep_class(&queue->_xmit_lock, dev->type);
7481 queue->xmit_lock_owner = -1;
7482 netdev_queue_numa_node_write(queue, NUMA_NO_NODE);
7483 queue->dev = dev;
7484#ifdef CONFIG_BQL
7485 dql_init(&queue->dql, HZ);
7486#endif
7487}
7488
7489static void netif_free_tx_queues(struct net_device *dev)
7490{
7491 kvfree(dev->_tx);
7492}
7493
7494static int netif_alloc_netdev_queues(struct net_device *dev)
7495{
7496 unsigned int count = dev->num_tx_queues;
7497 struct netdev_queue *tx;
7498 size_t sz = count * sizeof(*tx);
7499
7500 if (count < 1 || count > 0xffff)
7501 return -EINVAL;
7502
7503 tx = kvzalloc(sz, GFP_KERNEL | __GFP_RETRY_MAYFAIL);
7504 if (!tx)
7505 return -ENOMEM;
7506
7507 dev->_tx = tx;
7508
7509 netdev_for_each_tx_queue(dev, netdev_init_one_queue, NULL);
7510 spin_lock_init(&dev->tx_global_lock);
7511
7512 return 0;
7513}
7514
7515void netif_tx_stop_all_queues(struct net_device *dev)
7516{
7517 unsigned int i;
7518
7519 for (i = 0; i < dev->num_tx_queues; i++) {
7520 struct netdev_queue *txq = netdev_get_tx_queue(dev, i);
7521
7522 netif_tx_stop_queue(txq);
7523 }
7524}
7525EXPORT_SYMBOL(netif_tx_stop_all_queues);
7526
7527/**
7528 * register_netdevice - register a network device
7529 * @dev: device to register
7530 *
7531 * Take a completed network device structure and add it to the kernel
7532 * interfaces. A %NETDEV_REGISTER message is sent to the netdev notifier
7533 * chain. 0 is returned on success. A negative errno code is returned
7534 * on a failure to set up the device, or if the name is a duplicate.
7535 *
7536 * Callers must hold the rtnl semaphore. You may want
7537 * register_netdev() instead of this.
7538 *
7539 * BUGS:
7540 * The locking appears insufficient to guarantee two parallel registers
7541 * will not get the same name.
7542 */
7543
7544int register_netdevice(struct net_device *dev)
7545{
7546 int ret;
7547 struct net *net = dev_net(dev);
7548
7549 BUG_ON(dev_boot_phase);
7550 ASSERT_RTNL();
7551
7552 might_sleep();
7553
7554 /* When net_device's are persistent, this will be fatal. */
7555 BUG_ON(dev->reg_state != NETREG_UNINITIALIZED);
7556 BUG_ON(!net);
7557
7558 spin_lock_init(&dev->addr_list_lock);
7559 netdev_set_addr_lockdep_class(dev);
7560
7561 ret = dev_get_valid_name(net, dev, dev->name);
7562 if (ret < 0)
7563 goto out;
7564
7565 /* Init, if this function is available */
7566 if (dev->netdev_ops->ndo_init) {
7567 ret = dev->netdev_ops->ndo_init(dev);
7568 if (ret) {
7569 if (ret > 0)
7570 ret = -EIO;
7571 goto out;
7572 }
7573 }
7574
7575 if (((dev->hw_features | dev->features) &
7576 NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_FILTER) &&
7577 (!dev->netdev_ops->ndo_vlan_rx_add_vid ||
7578 !dev->netdev_ops->ndo_vlan_rx_kill_vid)) {
7579 netdev_WARN(dev, "Buggy VLAN acceleration in driver!\n");
7580 ret = -EINVAL;
7581 goto err_uninit;
7582 }
7583
7584 ret = -EBUSY;
7585 if (!dev->ifindex)
7586 dev->ifindex = dev_new_index(net);
7587 else if (__dev_get_by_index(net, dev->ifindex))
7588 goto err_uninit;
7589
7590 /* Transfer changeable features to wanted_features and enable
7591 * software offloads (GSO and GRO).
7592 */
7593 dev->hw_features |= NETIF_F_SOFT_FEATURES;
7594 dev->features |= NETIF_F_SOFT_FEATURES;
7595
7596 if (dev->netdev_ops->ndo_udp_tunnel_add) {
7597 dev->features |= NETIF_F_RX_UDP_TUNNEL_PORT;
7598 dev->hw_features |= NETIF_F_RX_UDP_TUNNEL_PORT;
7599 }
7600
7601 dev->wanted_features = dev->features & dev->hw_features;
7602
7603 if (!(dev->flags & IFF_LOOPBACK))
7604 dev->hw_features |= NETIF_F_NOCACHE_COPY;
7605
7606 /* If IPv4 TCP segmentation offload is supported we should also
7607 * allow the device to enable segmenting the frame with the option
7608 * of ignoring a static IP ID value. This doesn't enable the
7609 * feature itself but allows the user to enable it later.
7610 */
7611 if (dev->hw_features & NETIF_F_TSO)
7612 dev->hw_features |= NETIF_F_TSO_MANGLEID;
7613 if (dev->vlan_features & NETIF_F_TSO)
7614 dev->vlan_features |= NETIF_F_TSO_MANGLEID;
7615 if (dev->mpls_features & NETIF_F_TSO)
7616 dev->mpls_features |= NETIF_F_TSO_MANGLEID;
7617 if (dev->hw_enc_features & NETIF_F_TSO)
7618 dev->hw_enc_features |= NETIF_F_TSO_MANGLEID;
7619
7620 /* Make NETIF_F_HIGHDMA inheritable to VLAN devices.
7621 */
7622 dev->vlan_features |= NETIF_F_HIGHDMA;
7623
7624 /* Make NETIF_F_SG inheritable to tunnel devices.
7625 */
7626 dev->hw_enc_features |= NETIF_F_SG | NETIF_F_GSO_PARTIAL;
7627
7628 /* Make NETIF_F_SG inheritable to MPLS.
7629 */
7630 dev->mpls_features |= NETIF_F_SG;
7631
7632 ret = call_netdevice_notifiers(NETDEV_POST_INIT, dev);
7633 ret = notifier_to_errno(ret);
7634 if (ret)
7635 goto err_uninit;
7636
7637 ret = netdev_register_kobject(dev);
7638 if (ret)
7639 goto err_uninit;
7640 dev->reg_state = NETREG_REGISTERED;
7641
7642 __netdev_update_features(dev);
7643
7644 /*
7645 * Default initial state at registry is that the
7646 * device is present.
7647 */
7648
7649 set_bit(__LINK_STATE_PRESENT, &dev->state);
7650
7651 linkwatch_init_dev(dev);
7652
7653 dev_init_scheduler(dev);
7654 dev_hold(dev);
7655 list_netdevice(dev);
7656 add_device_randomness(dev->dev_addr, dev->addr_len);
7657
7658 /* If the device has permanent device address, driver should
7659 * set dev_addr and also addr_assign_type should be set to
7660 * NET_ADDR_PERM (default value).
7661 */
7662 if (dev->addr_assign_type == NET_ADDR_PERM)
7663 memcpy(dev->perm_addr, dev->dev_addr, dev->addr_len);
7664
7665 /* Notify protocols, that a new device appeared. */
7666 ret = call_netdevice_notifiers(NETDEV_REGISTER, dev);
7667 ret = notifier_to_errno(ret);
7668 if (ret) {
7669 rollback_registered(dev);
7670 dev->reg_state = NETREG_UNREGISTERED;
7671 }
7672 /*
7673 * Prevent userspace races by waiting until the network
7674 * device is fully setup before sending notifications.
7675 */
7676 if (!dev->rtnl_link_ops ||
7677 dev->rtnl_link_state == RTNL_LINK_INITIALIZED)
7678 rtmsg_ifinfo(RTM_NEWLINK, dev, ~0U, GFP_KERNEL);
7679
7680out:
7681 return ret;
7682
7683err_uninit:
7684 if (dev->netdev_ops->ndo_uninit)
7685 dev->netdev_ops->ndo_uninit(dev);
7686 if (dev->priv_destructor)
7687 dev->priv_destructor(dev);
7688 goto out;
7689}
7690EXPORT_SYMBOL(register_netdevice);
7691
7692/**
7693 * init_dummy_netdev - init a dummy network device for NAPI
7694 * @dev: device to init
7695 *
7696 * This takes a network device structure and initialize the minimum
7697 * amount of fields so it can be used to schedule NAPI polls without
7698 * registering a full blown interface. This is to be used by drivers
7699 * that need to tie several hardware interfaces to a single NAPI
7700 * poll scheduler due to HW limitations.
7701 */
7702int init_dummy_netdev(struct net_device *dev)
7703{
7704 /* Clear everything. Note we don't initialize spinlocks
7705 * are they aren't supposed to be taken by any of the
7706 * NAPI code and this dummy netdev is supposed to be
7707 * only ever used for NAPI polls
7708 */
7709 memset(dev, 0, sizeof(struct net_device));
7710
7711 /* make sure we BUG if trying to hit standard
7712 * register/unregister code path
7713 */
7714 dev->reg_state = NETREG_DUMMY;
7715
7716 /* NAPI wants this */
7717 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&dev->napi_list);
7718
7719 /* a dummy interface is started by default */
7720 set_bit(__LINK_STATE_PRESENT, &dev->state);
7721 set_bit(__LINK_STATE_START, &dev->state);
7722
7723 /* Note : We dont allocate pcpu_refcnt for dummy devices,
7724 * because users of this 'device' dont need to change
7725 * its refcount.
7726 */
7727
7728 return 0;
7729}
7730EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(init_dummy_netdev);
7731
7732
7733/**
7734 * register_netdev - register a network device
7735 * @dev: device to register
7736 *
7737 * Take a completed network device structure and add it to the kernel
7738 * interfaces. A %NETDEV_REGISTER message is sent to the netdev notifier
7739 * chain. 0 is returned on success. A negative errno code is returned
7740 * on a failure to set up the device, or if the name is a duplicate.
7741 *
7742 * This is a wrapper around register_netdevice that takes the rtnl semaphore
7743 * and expands the device name if you passed a format string to
7744 * alloc_netdev.
7745 */
7746int register_netdev(struct net_device *dev)
7747{
7748 int err;
7749
7750 rtnl_lock();
7751 err = register_netdevice(dev);
7752 rtnl_unlock();
7753 return err;
7754}
7755EXPORT_SYMBOL(register_netdev);
7756
7757int netdev_refcnt_read(const struct net_device *dev)
7758{
7759 int i, refcnt = 0;
7760
7761 for_each_possible_cpu(i)
7762 refcnt += *per_cpu_ptr(dev->pcpu_refcnt, i);
7763 return refcnt;
7764}
7765EXPORT_SYMBOL(netdev_refcnt_read);
7766
7767/**
7768 * netdev_wait_allrefs - wait until all references are gone.
7769 * @dev: target net_device
7770 *
7771 * This is called when unregistering network devices.
7772 *
7773 * Any protocol or device that holds a reference should register
7774 * for netdevice notification, and cleanup and put back the
7775 * reference if they receive an UNREGISTER event.
7776 * We can get stuck here if buggy protocols don't correctly
7777 * call dev_put.
7778 */
7779static void netdev_wait_allrefs(struct net_device *dev)
7780{
7781 unsigned long rebroadcast_time, warning_time;
7782 int refcnt;
7783
7784 linkwatch_forget_dev(dev);
7785
7786 rebroadcast_time = warning_time = jiffies;
7787 refcnt = netdev_refcnt_read(dev);
7788
7789 while (refcnt != 0) {
7790 if (time_after(jiffies, rebroadcast_time + 1 * HZ)) {
7791 rtnl_lock();
7792
7793 /* Rebroadcast unregister notification */
7794 call_netdevice_notifiers(NETDEV_UNREGISTER, dev);
7795
7796 __rtnl_unlock();
7797 rcu_barrier();
7798 rtnl_lock();
7799
7800 call_netdevice_notifiers(NETDEV_UNREGISTER_FINAL, dev);
7801 if (test_bit(__LINK_STATE_LINKWATCH_PENDING,
7802 &dev->state)) {
7803 /* We must not have linkwatch events
7804 * pending on unregister. If this
7805 * happens, we simply run the queue
7806 * unscheduled, resulting in a noop
7807 * for this device.
7808 */
7809 linkwatch_run_queue();
7810 }
7811
7812 __rtnl_unlock();
7813
7814 rebroadcast_time = jiffies;
7815 }
7816
7817 msleep(250);
7818
7819 refcnt = netdev_refcnt_read(dev);
7820
7821 if (time_after(jiffies, warning_time + 10 * HZ)) {
7822 pr_emerg("unregister_netdevice: waiting for %s to become free. Usage count = %d\n",
7823 dev->name, refcnt);
7824 warning_time = jiffies;
7825 }
7826 }
7827}
7828
7829/* The sequence is:
7830 *
7831 * rtnl_lock();
7832 * ...
7833 * register_netdevice(x1);
7834 * register_netdevice(x2);
7835 * ...
7836 * unregister_netdevice(y1);
7837 * unregister_netdevice(y2);
7838 * ...
7839 * rtnl_unlock();
7840 * free_netdev(y1);
7841 * free_netdev(y2);
7842 *
7843 * We are invoked by rtnl_unlock().
7844 * This allows us to deal with problems:
7845 * 1) We can delete sysfs objects which invoke hotplug
7846 * without deadlocking with linkwatch via keventd.
7847 * 2) Since we run with the RTNL semaphore not held, we can sleep
7848 * safely in order to wait for the netdev refcnt to drop to zero.
7849 *
7850 * We must not return until all unregister events added during
7851 * the interval the lock was held have been completed.
7852 */
7853void netdev_run_todo(void)
7854{
7855 struct list_head list;
7856
7857 /* Snapshot list, allow later requests */
7858 list_replace_init(&net_todo_list, &list);
7859
7860 __rtnl_unlock();
7861
7862
7863 /* Wait for rcu callbacks to finish before next phase */
7864 if (!list_empty(&list))
7865 rcu_barrier();
7866
7867 while (!list_empty(&list)) {
7868 struct net_device *dev
7869 = list_first_entry(&list, struct net_device, todo_list);
7870 list_del(&dev->todo_list);
7871
7872 rtnl_lock();
7873 call_netdevice_notifiers(NETDEV_UNREGISTER_FINAL, dev);
7874 __rtnl_unlock();
7875
7876 if (unlikely(dev->reg_state != NETREG_UNREGISTERING)) {
7877 pr_err("network todo '%s' but state %d\n",
7878 dev->name, dev->reg_state);
7879 dump_stack();
7880 continue;
7881 }
7882
7883 dev->reg_state = NETREG_UNREGISTERED;
7884
7885 netdev_wait_allrefs(dev);
7886
7887 /* paranoia */
7888 BUG_ON(netdev_refcnt_read(dev));
7889 BUG_ON(!list_empty(&dev->ptype_all));
7890 BUG_ON(!list_empty(&dev->ptype_specific));
7891 WARN_ON(rcu_access_pointer(dev->ip_ptr));
7892 WARN_ON(rcu_access_pointer(dev->ip6_ptr));
7893 WARN_ON(dev->dn_ptr);
7894
7895 if (dev->priv_destructor)
7896 dev->priv_destructor(dev);
7897 if (dev->needs_free_netdev)
7898 free_netdev(dev);
7899
7900 /* Report a network device has been unregistered */
7901 rtnl_lock();
7902 dev_net(dev)->dev_unreg_count--;
7903 __rtnl_unlock();
7904 wake_up(&netdev_unregistering_wq);
7905
7906 /* Free network device */
7907 kobject_put(&dev->dev.kobj);
7908 }
7909}
7910
7911/* Convert net_device_stats to rtnl_link_stats64. rtnl_link_stats64 has
7912 * all the same fields in the same order as net_device_stats, with only
7913 * the type differing, but rtnl_link_stats64 may have additional fields
7914 * at the end for newer counters.
7915 */
7916void netdev_stats_to_stats64(struct rtnl_link_stats64 *stats64,
7917 const struct net_device_stats *netdev_stats)
7918{
7919#if BITS_PER_LONG == 64
7920 BUILD_BUG_ON(sizeof(*stats64) < sizeof(*netdev_stats));
7921 memcpy(stats64, netdev_stats, sizeof(*netdev_stats));
7922 /* zero out counters that only exist in rtnl_link_stats64 */
7923 memset((char *)stats64 + sizeof(*netdev_stats), 0,
7924 sizeof(*stats64) - sizeof(*netdev_stats));
7925#else
7926 size_t i, n = sizeof(*netdev_stats) / sizeof(unsigned long);
7927 const unsigned long *src = (const unsigned long *)netdev_stats;
7928 u64 *dst = (u64 *)stats64;
7929
7930 BUILD_BUG_ON(n > sizeof(*stats64) / sizeof(u64));
7931 for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
7932 dst[i] = src[i];
7933 /* zero out counters that only exist in rtnl_link_stats64 */
7934 memset((char *)stats64 + n * sizeof(u64), 0,
7935 sizeof(*stats64) - n * sizeof(u64));
7936#endif
7937}
7938EXPORT_SYMBOL(netdev_stats_to_stats64);
7939
7940/**
7941 * dev_get_stats - get network device statistics
7942 * @dev: device to get statistics from
7943 * @storage: place to store stats
7944 *
7945 * Get network statistics from device. Return @storage.
7946 * The device driver may provide its own method by setting
7947 * dev->netdev_ops->get_stats64 or dev->netdev_ops->get_stats;
7948 * otherwise the internal statistics structure is used.
7949 */
7950struct rtnl_link_stats64 *dev_get_stats(struct net_device *dev,
7951 struct rtnl_link_stats64 *storage)
7952{
7953 const struct net_device_ops *ops = dev->netdev_ops;
7954
7955 if (ops->ndo_get_stats64) {
7956 memset(storage, 0, sizeof(*storage));
7957 ops->ndo_get_stats64(dev, storage);
7958 } else if (ops->ndo_get_stats) {
7959 netdev_stats_to_stats64(storage, ops->ndo_get_stats(dev));
7960 } else {
7961 netdev_stats_to_stats64(storage, &dev->stats);
7962 }
7963 storage->rx_dropped += (unsigned long)atomic_long_read(&dev->rx_dropped);
7964 storage->tx_dropped += (unsigned long)atomic_long_read(&dev->tx_dropped);
7965 storage->rx_nohandler += (unsigned long)atomic_long_read(&dev->rx_nohandler);
7966 return storage;
7967}
7968EXPORT_SYMBOL(dev_get_stats);
7969
7970struct netdev_queue *dev_ingress_queue_create(struct net_device *dev)
7971{
7972 struct netdev_queue *queue = dev_ingress_queue(dev);
7973
7974#ifdef CONFIG_NET_CLS_ACT
7975 if (queue)
7976 return queue;
7977 queue = kzalloc(sizeof(*queue), GFP_KERNEL);
7978 if (!queue)
7979 return NULL;
7980 netdev_init_one_queue(dev, queue, NULL);
7981 RCU_INIT_POINTER(queue->qdisc, &noop_qdisc);
7982 queue->qdisc_sleeping = &noop_qdisc;
7983 rcu_assign_pointer(dev->ingress_queue, queue);
7984#endif
7985 return queue;
7986}

7988static const struct ethtool_ops default_ethtool_ops;
7989
7990void netdev_set_default_ethtool_ops(struct net_device *dev,
7991 const struct ethtool_ops *ops)
7992{
7993 if (dev->ethtool_ops == &default_ethtool_ops)
7994 dev->ethtool_ops = ops;
7995}
7996EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(netdev_set_default_ethtool_ops);
7997
7998void netdev_freemem(struct net_device *dev)
7999{
8000 char *addr = (char *)dev - dev->padded;
8001
8002 kvfree(addr);
8003}
8004
8005/**
8006 * alloc_netdev_mqs - allocate network device
8007 * @sizeof_priv: size of private data to allocate space for
8008 * @name: device name format string
8009 * @name_assign_type: origin of device name
8010 * @setup: callback to initialize device
8011 * @txqs: the number of TX subqueues to allocate
8012 * @rxqs: the number of RX subqueues to allocate
8013 *
8014 * Allocates a struct net_device with private data area for driver use
8015 * and performs basic initialization. Also allocates subqueue structs
8016 * for each queue on the device.
8017 */
8018struct net_device *alloc_netdev_mqs(int sizeof_priv, const char *name,
8019 unsigned char name_assign_type,
8020 void (*setup)(struct net_device *),
8021 unsigned int txqs, unsigned int rxqs)
8022{
8023 struct net_device *dev;
8024 size_t alloc_size;
8025 struct net_device *p;
8026
8027 BUG_ON(strlen(name) >= sizeof(dev->name));
8028
8029 if (txqs < 1) {
8030 pr_err("alloc_netdev: Unable to allocate device with zero queues\n");
8031 return NULL;
8032 }
8033
8034#ifdef CONFIG_SYSFS
8035 if (rxqs < 1) {
8036 pr_err("alloc_netdev: Unable to allocate device with zero RX queues\n");
8037 return NULL;
8038 }
8039#endif
8040
8041 alloc_size = sizeof(struct net_device);
8042 if (sizeof_priv) {
8043 /* ensure 32-byte alignment of private area */
8044 alloc_size = ALIGN(alloc_size, NETDEV_ALIGN);
8045 alloc_size += sizeof_priv;
8046 }
8047 /* ensure 32-byte alignment of whole construct */
8048 alloc_size += NETDEV_ALIGN - 1;
8049
8050 p = kvzalloc(alloc_size, GFP_KERNEL | __GFP_RETRY_MAYFAIL);
8051 if (!p)
8052 return NULL;
8053
8054 dev = PTR_ALIGN(p, NETDEV_ALIGN);
8055 dev->padded = (char *)dev - (char *)p;
8056
8057 dev->pcpu_refcnt = alloc_percpu(int);
8058 if (!dev->pcpu_refcnt)
8059 goto free_dev;
8060
8061 if (dev_addr_init(dev))
8062 goto free_pcpu;
8063
8064 dev_mc_init(dev);
8065 dev_uc_init(dev);
8066
8067 dev_net_set(dev, &init_net);
8068
8069 dev->gso_max_size = GSO_MAX_SIZE;
8070 dev->gso_max_segs = GSO_MAX_SEGS;
8071
8072 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&dev->napi_list);
8073 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&dev->unreg_list);
8074 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&dev->close_list);
8075 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&dev->link_watch_list);
8076 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&dev->adj_list.upper);
8077 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&dev->adj_list.lower);
8078 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&dev->ptype_all);
8079 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&dev->ptype_specific);
8080#ifdef CONFIG_NET_SCHED
8081 hash_init(dev->qdisc_hash);
8082#endif
8083 dev->priv_flags = IFF_XMIT_DST_RELEASE | IFF_XMIT_DST_RELEASE_PERM;
8084 setup(dev);
8085
8086 if (!dev->tx_queue_len) {
8087 dev->priv_flags |= IFF_NO_QUEUE;
8088 dev->tx_queue_len = DEFAULT_TX_QUEUE_LEN;
8089 }
8090
8091 dev->num_tx_queues = txqs;
8092 dev->real_num_tx_queues = txqs;
8093 if (netif_alloc_netdev_queues(dev))
8094 goto free_all;
8095
8096#ifdef CONFIG_SYSFS
8097 dev->num_rx_queues = rxqs;
8098 dev->real_num_rx_queues = rxqs;
8099 if (netif_alloc_rx_queues(dev))
8100 goto free_all;
8101#endif
8102
8103 strcpy(dev->name, name);
8104 dev->name_assign_type = name_assign_type;
8105 dev->group = INIT_NETDEV_GROUP;
8106 if (!dev->ethtool_ops)
8107 dev->ethtool_ops = &default_ethtool_ops;
8108
8109 nf_hook_ingress_init(dev);
8110
8111 return dev;
8112
8113free_all:
8114 free_netdev(dev);
8115 return NULL;
8116
8117free_pcpu:
8118 free_percpu(dev->pcpu_refcnt);
8119free_dev:
8120 netdev_freemem(dev);
8121 return NULL;
8122}
8123EXPORT_SYMBOL(alloc_netdev_mqs);
8124
8125/**
8126 * free_netdev - free network device
8127 * @dev: device
8128 *
8129 * This function does the last stage of destroying an allocated device
8130 * interface. The reference to the device object is released. If this
8131 * is the last reference then it will be freed.Must be called in process
8132 * context.
8133 */
8134void free_netdev(struct net_device *dev)
8135{
8136 struct napi_struct *p, *n;
8137 struct bpf_prog *prog;
8138
8139 might_sleep();
8140 netif_free_tx_queues(dev);
8141#ifdef CONFIG_SYSFS
8142 kvfree(dev->_rx);
8143#endif
8144
8145 kfree(rcu_dereference_protected(dev->ingress_queue, 1));
8146
8147 /* Flush device addresses */
8148 dev_addr_flush(dev);
8149
8150 list_for_each_entry_safe(p, n, &dev->napi_list, dev_list)
8151 netif_napi_del(p);
8152
8153 free_percpu(dev->pcpu_refcnt);
8154 dev->pcpu_refcnt = NULL;
8155
8156 prog = rcu_dereference_protected(dev->xdp_prog, 1);
8157 if (prog) {
8158 bpf_prog_put(prog);
8159 static_key_slow_dec(&generic_xdp_needed);
8160 }
8161
8162 /* Compatibility with error handling in drivers */
8163 if (dev->reg_state == NETREG_UNINITIALIZED) {
8164 netdev_freemem(dev);
8165 return;
8166 }
8167
8168 BUG_ON(dev->reg_state != NETREG_UNREGISTERED);
8169 dev->reg_state = NETREG_RELEASED;
8170
8171 /* will free via device release */
8172 put_device(&dev->dev);
8173}
8174EXPORT_SYMBOL(free_netdev);
8175
8176/**
8177 * synchronize_net - Synchronize with packet receive processing
8178 *
8179 * Wait for packets currently being received to be done.
8180 * Does not block later packets from starting.
8181 */
8182void synchronize_net(void)
8183{
8184 might_sleep();
8185 if (rtnl_is_locked())
8186 synchronize_rcu_expedited();
8187 else
8188 synchronize_rcu();
8189}
8190EXPORT_SYMBOL(synchronize_net);
8191
8192/**
8193 * unregister_netdevice_queue - remove device from the kernel
8194 * @dev: device
8195 * @head: list
8196 *
8197 * This function shuts down a device interface and removes it
8198 * from the kernel tables.
8199 * If head not NULL, device is queued to be unregistered later.
8200 *
8201 * Callers must hold the rtnl semaphore. You may want
8202 * unregister_netdev() instead of this.
8203 */
8204
8205void unregister_netdevice_queue(struct net_device *dev, struct list_head *head)
8206{
8207 ASSERT_RTNL();
8208
8209 if (head) {
8210 list_move_tail(&dev->unreg_list, head);
8211 } else {
8212 rollback_registered(dev);
8213 /* Finish processing unregister after unlock */
8214 net_set_todo(dev);
8215 }
8216}
8217EXPORT_SYMBOL(unregister_netdevice_queue);
8218
8219/**
8220 * unregister_netdevice_many - unregister many devices
8221 * @head: list of devices
8222 *
8223 * Note: As most callers use a stack allocated list_head,
8224 * we force a list_del() to make sure stack wont be corrupted later.
8225 */
8226void unregister_netdevice_many(struct list_head *head)
8227{
8228 struct net_device *dev;
8229
8230 if (!list_empty(head)) {
8231 rollback_registered_many(head);
8232 list_for_each_entry(dev, head, unreg_list)
8233 net_set_todo(dev);
8234 list_del(head);
8235 }
8236}
8237EXPORT_SYMBOL(unregister_netdevice_many);
8238
8239/**
8240 * unregister_netdev - remove device from the kernel
8241 * @dev: device
8242 *
8243 * This function shuts down a device interface and removes it
8244 * from the kernel tables.
8245 *
8246 * This is just a wrapper for unregister_netdevice that takes
8247 * the rtnl semaphore. In general you want to use this and not
8248 * unregister_netdevice.
8249 */
8250void unregister_netdev(struct net_device *dev)
8251{
8252 rtnl_lock();
8253 unregister_netdevice(dev);
8254 rtnl_unlock();
8255}
8256EXPORT_SYMBOL(unregister_netdev);
8257
8258/**
8259 * dev_change_net_namespace - move device to different nethost namespace
8260 * @dev: device
8261 * @net: network namespace
8262 * @pat: If not NULL name pattern to try if the current device name
8263 * is already taken in the destination network namespace.
8264 *
8265 * This function shuts down a device interface and moves it
8266 * to a new network namespace. On success 0 is returned, on
8267 * a failure a netagive errno code is returned.
8268 *
8269 * Callers must hold the rtnl semaphore.
8270 */
8271
8272int dev_change_net_namespace(struct net_device *dev, struct net *net, const char *pat)
8273{
8274 int err;
8275
8276 ASSERT_RTNL();
8277
8278 /* Don't allow namespace local devices to be moved. */
8279 err = -EINVAL;
8280 if (dev->features & NETIF_F_NETNS_LOCAL)
8281 goto out;
8282
8283 /* Ensure the device has been registrered */
8284 if (dev->reg_state != NETREG_REGISTERED)
8285 goto out;
8286
8287 /* Get out if there is nothing todo */
8288 err = 0;
8289 if (net_eq(dev_net(dev), net))
8290 goto out;
8291
8292 /* Pick the destination device name, and ensure
8293 * we can use it in the destination network namespace.
8294 */
8295 err = -EEXIST;
8296 if (__dev_get_by_name(net, dev->name)) {
8297 /* We get here if we can't use the current device name */
8298 if (!pat)
8299 goto out;
8300 if (dev_get_valid_name(net, dev, pat) < 0)
8301 goto out;
8302 }
8303
8304 /*
8305 * And now a mini version of register_netdevice unregister_netdevice.
8306 */
8307
8308 /* If device is running close it first. */
8309 dev_close(dev);
8310
8311 /* And unlink it from device chain */
8312 err = -ENODEV;
8313 unlist_netdevice(dev);
8314
8315 synchronize_net();
8316
8317 /* Shutdown queueing discipline. */
8318 dev_shutdown(dev);
8319
8320 /* Notify protocols, that we are about to destroy
8321 * this device. They should clean all the things.
8322 *
8323 * Note that dev->reg_state stays at NETREG_REGISTERED.
8324 * This is wanted because this way 8021q and macvlan know
8325 * the device is just moving and can keep their slaves up.
8326 */
8327 call_netdevice_notifiers(NETDEV_UNREGISTER, dev);
8328 rcu_barrier();
8329 call_netdevice_notifiers(NETDEV_UNREGISTER_FINAL, dev);
8330 rtmsg_ifinfo(RTM_DELLINK, dev, ~0U, GFP_KERNEL);
8331
8332 /*
8333 * Flush the unicast and multicast chains
8334 */
8335 dev_uc_flush(dev);
8336 dev_mc_flush(dev);
8337
8338 /* Send a netdev-removed uevent to the old namespace */
8339 kobject_uevent(&dev->dev.kobj, KOBJ_REMOVE);
8340 netdev_adjacent_del_links(dev);
8341
8342 /* Actually switch the network namespace */
8343 dev_net_set(dev, net);
8344
8345 /* If there is an ifindex conflict assign a new one */
8346 if (__dev_get_by_index(net, dev->ifindex))
8347 dev->ifindex = dev_new_index(net);
8348
8349 /* Send a netdev-add uevent to the new namespace */
8350 kobject_uevent(&dev->dev.kobj, KOBJ_ADD);
8351 netdev_adjacent_add_links(dev);
8352
8353 /* Fixup kobjects */
8354 err = device_rename(&dev->dev, dev->name);
8355 WARN_ON(err);
8356
8357 /* Add the device back in the hashes */
8358 list_netdevice(dev);
8359
8360 /* Notify protocols, that a new device appeared. */
8361 call_netdevice_notifiers(NETDEV_REGISTER, dev);
8362
8363 /*
8364 * Prevent userspace races by waiting until the network
8365 * device is fully setup before sending notifications.
8366 */
8367 rtmsg_ifinfo(RTM_NEWLINK, dev, ~0U, GFP_KERNEL);
8368
8369 synchronize_net();
8370 err = 0;
8371out:
8372 return err;
8373}
8374EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(dev_change_net_namespace);
8375
8376static int dev_cpu_dead(unsigned int oldcpu)
8377{
8378 struct sk_buff **list_skb;
8379 struct sk_buff *skb;
8380 unsigned int cpu;
8381 struct softnet_data *sd, *oldsd, *remsd = NULL;
8382
8383 local_irq_disable();
8384 cpu = smp_processor_id();
8385 sd = &per_cpu(softnet_data, cpu);
8386 oldsd = &per_cpu(softnet_data, oldcpu);
8387
8388 /* Find end of our completion_queue. */
8389 list_skb = &sd->completion_queue;
8390 while (*list_skb)
8391 list_skb = &(*list_skb)->next;
8392 /* Append completion queue from offline CPU. */
8393 *list_skb = oldsd->completion_queue;
8394 oldsd->completion_queue = NULL;
8395
8396 /* Append output queue from offline CPU. */
8397 if (oldsd->output_queue) {
8398 *sd->output_queue_tailp = oldsd->output_queue;
8399 sd->output_queue_tailp = oldsd->output_queue_tailp;
8400 oldsd->output_queue = NULL;
8401 oldsd->output_queue_tailp = &oldsd->output_queue;
8402 }
8403 /* Append NAPI poll list from offline CPU, with one exception :
8404 * process_backlog() must be called by cpu owning percpu backlog.
8405 * We properly handle process_queue & input_pkt_queue later.
8406 */
8407 while (!list_empty(&oldsd->poll_list)) {
8408 struct napi_struct *napi = list_first_entry(&oldsd->poll_list,
8409 struct napi_struct,
8410 poll_list);
8411
8412 list_del_init(&napi->poll_list);
8413 if (napi->poll == process_backlog)
8414 napi->state = 0;
8415 else
8416 ____napi_schedule(sd, napi);
8417 }
8418
8419 raise_softirq_irqoff(NET_TX_SOFTIRQ);
8420 local_irq_enable();
8421
8422#ifdef CONFIG_RPS
8423 remsd = oldsd->rps_ipi_list;
8424 oldsd->rps_ipi_list = NULL;
8425#endif
8426 /* send out pending IPI's on offline CPU */
8427 net_rps_send_ipi(remsd);
8428
8429 /* Process offline CPU's input_pkt_queue */
8430 while ((skb = __skb_dequeue(&oldsd->process_queue))) {
8431 netif_rx_ni(skb);
8432 input_queue_head_incr(oldsd);
8433 }
8434 while ((skb = skb_dequeue(&oldsd->input_pkt_queue))) {
8435 netif_rx_ni(skb);
8436 input_queue_head_incr(oldsd);
8437 }
8438
8439 return 0;
8440}
8441
8442/**
8443 * netdev_increment_features - increment feature set by one
8444 * @all: current feature set
8445 * @one: new feature set
8446 * @mask: mask feature set
8447 *
8448 * Computes a new feature set after adding a device with feature set
8449 * @one to the master device with current feature set @all. Will not
8450 * enable anything that is off in @mask. Returns the new feature set.
8451 */
8452netdev_features_t netdev_increment_features(netdev_features_t all,
8453 netdev_features_t one, netdev_features_t mask)
8454{
8455 if (mask & NETIF_F_HW_CSUM)
8456 mask |= NETIF_F_CSUM_MASK;
8457 mask |= NETIF_F_VLAN_CHALLENGED;
8458
8459 all |= one & (NETIF_F_ONE_FOR_ALL | NETIF_F_CSUM_MASK) & mask;
8460 all &= one | ~NETIF_F_ALL_FOR_ALL;
8461
8462 /* If one device supports hw checksumming, set for all. */
8463 if (all & NETIF_F_HW_CSUM)
8464 all &= ~(NETIF_F_CSUM_MASK & ~NETIF_F_HW_CSUM);
8465
8466 return all;
8467}
8468EXPORT_SYMBOL(netdev_increment_features);

8470static struct hlist_head * __net_init netdev_create_hash(void)
8471{
8472 int i;
8473 struct hlist_head *hash;
8474
8475 hash = kmalloc(sizeof(*hash) * NETDEV_HASHENTRIES, GFP_KERNEL);
8476 if (hash != NULL)
8477 for (i = 0; i < NETDEV_HASHENTRIES; i++)
8478 INIT_HLIST_HEAD(&hash[i]);
8479
8480 return hash;
8481}
8482
8483/* Initialize per network namespace state */
8484static int __net_init netdev_init(struct net *net)
8485{
8486 if (net != &init_net)
8487 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&net->dev_base_head);
8488
8489 net->dev_name_head = netdev_create_hash();
8490 if (net->dev_name_head == NULL)
8491 goto err_name;
8492
8493 net->dev_index_head = netdev_create_hash();
8494 if (net->dev_index_head == NULL)
8495 goto err_idx;
8496
8497 return 0;
8498
8499err_idx:
8500 kfree(net->dev_name_head);
8501err_name:
8502 return -ENOMEM;
8503}
8504
8505/**
8506 * netdev_drivername - network driver for the device
8507 * @dev: network device
8508 *
8509 * Determine network driver for device.
8510 */
8511const char *netdev_drivername(const struct net_device *dev)
8512{
8513 const struct device_driver *driver;
8514 const struct device *parent;
8515 const char *empty = "";
8516
8517 parent = dev->dev.parent;
8518 if (!parent)
8519 return empty;
8520
8521 driver = parent->driver;
8522 if (driver && driver->name)
8523 return driver->name;
8524 return empty;
8525}

8527static void __netdev_printk(const char *level, const struct net_device *dev,
8528 struct va_format *vaf)
8529{
8530 if (dev && dev->dev.parent) {
8531 dev_printk_emit(level[1] - '0',
8532 dev->dev.parent,
8533 "%s %s %s%s: %pV",
8534 dev_driver_string(dev->dev.parent),
8535 dev_name(dev->dev.parent),
8536 netdev_name(dev), netdev_reg_state(dev),
8537 vaf);
8538 } else if (dev) {
8539 printk("%s%s%s: %pV",
8540 level, netdev_name(dev), netdev_reg_state(dev), vaf);
8541 } else {
8542 printk("%s(NULL net_device): %pV", level, vaf);
8543 }
8544}
8545
8546void netdev_printk(const char *level, const struct net_device *dev,
8547 const char *format, ...)
8548{
8549 struct va_format vaf;
8550 va_list args;
8551
8552 va_start(args, format);
8553
8554 vaf.fmt = format;
8555 vaf.va = &args;
8556
8557 __netdev_printk(level, dev, &vaf);
8558
8559 va_end(args);
8560}
8561EXPORT_SYMBOL(netdev_printk);
8562
8563#define define_netdev_printk_level(func, level) \
8564void func(const struct net_device *dev, const char *fmt, ...) \
8565{ \
8566 struct va_format vaf; \
8567 va_list args; \
8568 \
8569 va_start(args, fmt); \
8570 \
8571 vaf.fmt = fmt; \
8572 vaf.va = &args; \
8573 \
8574 __netdev_printk(level, dev, &vaf); \
8575 \
8576 va_end(args); \
8577} \
8578EXPORT_SYMBOL(func);
8579
8580define_netdev_printk_level(netdev_emerg, KERN_EMERG);
8581define_netdev_printk_level(netdev_alert, KERN_ALERT);
8582define_netdev_printk_level(netdev_crit, KERN_CRIT);
8583define_netdev_printk_level(netdev_err, KERN_ERR);
8584define_netdev_printk_level(netdev_warn, KERN_WARNING);
8585define_netdev_printk_level(netdev_notice, KERN_NOTICE);
8586define_netdev_printk_level(netdev_info, KERN_INFO);

8588static void __net_exit netdev_exit(struct net *net)
8589{
8590 kfree(net->dev_name_head);
8591 kfree(net->dev_index_head);
8592}

8594static struct pernet_operations __net_initdata netdev_net_ops = {
8595 .init = netdev_init,
8596 .exit = netdev_exit,
8597};
8598
8599static void __net_exit default_device_exit(struct net *net)
8600{
8601 struct net_device *dev, *aux;
8602 /*
8603 * Push all migratable network devices back to the
8604 * initial network namespace
8605 */
8606 rtnl_lock();
8607 for_each_netdev_safe(net, dev, aux) {
8608 int err;
8609 char fb_name[IFNAMSIZ];
8610
8611 /* Ignore unmoveable devices (i.e. loopback) */
8612 if (dev->features & NETIF_F_NETNS_LOCAL)
8613 continue;
8614
8615 /* Leave virtual devices for the generic cleanup */
8616 if (dev->rtnl_link_ops)
8617 continue;
8618
8619 /* Push remaining network devices to init_net */
8620 snprintf(fb_name, IFNAMSIZ, "dev%d", dev->ifindex);
8621 err = dev_change_net_namespace(dev, &init_net, fb_name);
8622 if (err) {
8623 pr_emerg("%s: failed to move %s to init_net: %d\n",
8624 __func__, dev->name, err);
8625 BUG();
8626 }
8627 }
8628 rtnl_unlock();
8629}
8630
8631static void __net_exit rtnl_lock_unregistering(struct list_head *net_list)
8632{
8633 /* Return with the rtnl_lock held when there are no network
8634 * devices unregistering in any network namespace in net_list.
8635 */
8636 struct net *net;
8637 bool unregistering;
8638 DEFINE_WAIT_FUNC(wait, woken_wake_function);
8639
8640 add_wait_queue(&netdev_unregistering_wq, &wait);
8641 for (;;) {
8642 unregistering = false;
8643 rtnl_lock();
8644 list_for_each_entry(net, net_list, exit_list) {
8645 if (net->dev_unreg_count > 0) {
8646 unregistering = true;
8647 break;
8648 }
8649 }
8650 if (!unregistering)
8651 break;
8652 __rtnl_unlock();
8653
8654 wait_woken(&wait, TASK_UNINTERRUPTIBLE, MAX_SCHEDULE_TIMEOUT);
8655 }
8656 remove_wait_queue(&netdev_unregistering_wq, &wait);
8657}
8658
8659static void __net_exit default_device_exit_batch(struct list_head *net_list)
8660{
8661 /* At exit all network devices most be removed from a network
8662 * namespace. Do this in the reverse order of registration.
8663 * Do this across as many network namespaces as possible to
8664 * improve batching efficiency.
8665 */
8666 struct net_device *dev;
8667 struct net *net;
8668 LIST_HEAD(dev_kill_list);
8669
8670 /* To prevent network device cleanup code from dereferencing
8671 * loopback devices or network devices that have been freed
8672 * wait here for all pending unregistrations to complete,
8673 * before unregistring the loopback device and allowing the
8674 * network namespace be freed.
8675 *
8676 * The netdev todo list containing all network devices
8677 * unregistrations that happen in default_device_exit_batch
8678 * will run in the rtnl_unlock() at the end of
8679 * default_device_exit_batch.
8680 */
8681 rtnl_lock_unregistering(net_list);
8682 list_for_each_entry(net, net_list, exit_list) {
8683 for_each_netdev_reverse(net, dev) {
8684 if (dev->rtnl_link_ops && dev->rtnl_link_ops->dellink)
8685 dev->rtnl_link_ops->dellink(dev, &dev_kill_list);
8686 else
8687 unregister_netdevice_queue(dev, &dev_kill_list);
8688 }
8689 }
8690 unregister_netdevice_many(&dev_kill_list);
8691 rtnl_unlock();
8692}
8693
8694static struct pernet_operations __net_initdata default_device_ops = {
8695 .exit = default_device_exit,
8696 .exit_batch = default_device_exit_batch,
8697};
8698
8699/*
8700 * Initialize the DEV module. At boot time this walks the device list and
8701 * unhooks any devices that fail to initialise (normally hardware not
8702 * present) and leaves us with a valid list of present and active devices.
8703 *
8704 */
8705
8706/*
8707 * This is called single threaded during boot, so no need
8708 * to take the rtnl semaphore.
8709 */
8710static int __init net_dev_init(void)
8711{
8712 int i, rc = -ENOMEM;
8713
8714 BUG_ON(!dev_boot_phase);
8715
8716 if (dev_proc_init())
8717 goto out;
8718
8719 if (netdev_kobject_init())
8720 goto out;
8721
8722 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&ptype_all);
8723 for (i = 0; i < PTYPE_HASH_SIZE; i++)
8724 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&ptype_base[i]);
8725
8726 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&offload_base);
8727
8728 if (register_pernet_subsys(&netdev_net_ops))
8729 goto out;
8730
8731 /*
8732 * Initialise the packet receive queues.
8733 */
8734
8735 for_each_possible_cpu(i) {
8736 struct work_struct *flush = per_cpu_ptr(&flush_works, i);
8737 struct softnet_data *sd = &per_cpu(softnet_data, i);
8738
8739 INIT_WORK(flush, flush_backlog);
8740
8741 skb_queue_head_init(&sd->input_pkt_queue);
8742 skb_queue_head_init(&sd->process_queue);
8743 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&sd->poll_list);
8744 sd->output_queue_tailp = &sd->output_queue;
8745#ifdef CONFIG_RPS
8746 sd->csd.func = rps_trigger_softirq;
8747 sd->csd.info = sd;
8748 sd->cpu = i;
8749#endif
8750
8751 sd->backlog.poll = process_backlog;
8752 sd->backlog.weight = weight_p;
8753 }
8754
8755 dev_boot_phase = 0;
8756
8757 /* The loopback device is special if any other network devices
8758 * is present in a network namespace the loopback device must
8759 * be present. Since we now dynamically allocate and free the
8760 * loopback device ensure this invariant is maintained by
8761 * keeping the loopback device as the first device on the
8762 * list of network devices. Ensuring the loopback devices
8763 * is the first device that appears and the last network device
8764 * that disappears.
8765 */
8766 if (register_pernet_device(&loopback_net_ops))
8767 goto out;
8768
8769 if (register_pernet_device(&default_device_ops))
8770 goto out;
8771
8772 open_softirq(NET_TX_SOFTIRQ, net_tx_action);
8773 open_softirq(NET_RX_SOFTIRQ, net_rx_action);
8774
8775 rc = cpuhp_setup_state_nocalls(CPUHP_NET_DEV_DEAD, "net/dev:dead",
8776 NULL, dev_cpu_dead);
8777 WARN_ON(rc < 0);
8778 rc = 0;
8779out:
8780 return rc;
8781}
8782
8783subsys_initcall(net_dev_init);
